name: STAY CLOSE IN OUR SEMI-PRIVATE BUNK POD FOR 2
description:
BUNK Hotel Amsterdam is situated in the hip, up-and-coming neighbourhood of Amsterdam Noord, based in the former St. Rita church just 5 minutes from Amsterdam Central Station. BUNK bridges the gap between hotels and hostels by combining affordable luxury rooms and smartly designed semi-private pods, whilst creating a place for communal wonderment, with inclusive events housed in our sustainable restaurant and other shared areas. BUNK... a gathering place for travellers, locals and artists alike!

The space
On an adventure with your partner or a close friend? And looking for a low-cost option with a high level of privacy? Then treat yourself to our BUNK Pod for 2. It really takes the ‘s’ out of ‘hostel’. Because everything you need is right there, in your very own compact comfort zone.

Guest access
Our restaurant is the perfect place to hang out, all day long. After breakfast, pop open your laptop or meet for a nice lunch. Once the sun sets,
neighborhood_overview: Just minutes by free ferry from Central Station lies Amsterdam North. This neighbourhood is alive and kicking, bursting with cultural hotspots. Authentic urban life lives on, too, still undiscovered by tourists.The Saint Rita church has always been a place where the North comes together. Now, it’s also where you’ll find BUNK Amsterdam. This monumental building is now home to 296 guests, 106 rooms, 50 private pods, eight communal dinner tables and one teddy bear. So come to the North Side, where we have cookies, and company. On top of that, you’ll be sleeping in a church, a unique experience in Amsterdam!
host_about:
BUNK bridges the gap between hotels and hostels by combining affordable luxury rooms and smartly designed private bunk beds.
We converted two monumental churches into meeting places for travellers, locals and artists alike. We host inclusive social events in our sustainable restaurant and other communal spaces.

We aim to redefine hospitality by creating a place for communal wonderment. Where those who wander will start to wonder, triggered by true art, honest food and sincere smiles. We make comfort and design available to everyone, without the need for deep pockets. BUNK is where you can feel free to be your wonderfully weird self as you play your part in new stories you can take home with you.

neighborhood_overview:
Neighborhood Facts
Beginning at Vondelpark and continuing to the Amstel river, the Oud-Zuid and De Pijp neighborhoods have elegant homes on quiet leafy lanes and busy, lively streets with shopping and cafes. The two neighborhoods seem worlds apart but are right next door to each other.

Shopping in De Pijp & Oud-Zuid
Probably the most well-known street market in Amsterdam is the Albert Cuyp Markt, located right in the middle of de Pijp. This market is open six days per week and sells almost anything you might need. Toothpaste, tshirts, fresh pickles, sunglasses, vegetables, cheese, bicycle locks, scarves and stroopwafels are just a few of the items on hand. Albert Cuyp is a wonderful place to get those random items you can’t seem to find elsewhere, like rainbow shoelaces.

On Saturdays don’t miss the ZuiderMarkt, a biological open air market located at the corner of Jacob Obrechtstraat and Johannes Verhulststraat.

The Free spirit suite is 35 meters on top of the crane. This suite has two levels, no less than 38 square meters. So it’s spacious, 5 -star, high end luxury and beautifully decorated and equipped with all amenities.

The small panorama elevator stops right into your suite. Large windows provide an amazing view over Amsterdam and the river IJ. The port of Amsterdam is right in front of the crane.

The first floor is a spacious living area, furnished with art and design furniture. Hidden behind a characteristic sliding glass panel is a bathroom with a rain shower and toilet. The shower is decorated with antique parts of an ocean cruiser.

A staircase leads to the sleeping area with a King size bed and bath tube surrounded by paintings and design. Quality toiletries are offered. All suites have air-conditioning, free WIFI, 2 plasma television screens (bedroom & living).

The crane is one of the most significant developments of its time and has received unprecedented international media coverage to herald its uniqueness. There are several popular restaurants under the crane. We'll send a list with the restaurants and other nearby things to see and do.
host_about:
"Welcome to the Faralda Crane Hotel in Amsterdam"

 MAKE YOUR DREAMS COME TRUE

The Faralda Crane Hotel, hidden on top of the highest monumental harbour crane, three spacious 5- star suites.

“Faralda is Amsterdam’s best-kept secret”

Don't expect a mainstream hotel "You'll love it or you hate it"
It’s a crane! Faralda is a mind-blowing and a once in a lifetime experience. 
It’s excessive. Private & Invites only. 
Access is on request, Rent a suite with your Lover(s) and choose your suite: 
1. Free Spirit, 2. Secret Suite, 3. Mystique Suite (All rooms have a 360 view of Amsterdam).

“The Faralda Crane Hotel, the most Romantic & Inspiring place to stay”

Enjoy your romantic weekend discreetly, right in front of the crane and your suite  boats are sailing on the always busy river IJ. 

Enjoy the romantic 360 view over Amsterdam with the sunset up to the dunes at the end of the horizon. 

The former NDSM shipyard is a lively art district with numerous trendy restaurants, cafés and the largest graffiti museum in the world.

The panorama elevator to the top even stops right into your suite, The heated Jacuzzi is hidden on the top deck. “What happens in the crane, stays in the crane” 

Your stay is safe with us safe.

Canal View Amsterdam is beautifully located on the Brouwersgracht at the heart of the monumental 17th Century Canal Belt and on the border of the Jordaan. Brouwersgracht was dug in 1585. In 2007 the quiet and in all seasons splendid Brouwersgracht was choosen by the readers of the Amsterdam newspaper Het Parool as the most beautiful street of Amsterdam. In 2010 the Amsterdam Canal Belt area was placed on the UNESCO World Heritage list.

All major Amsterdam attractions are within walking distance: Haarlemmerstraat / Haarlemmerdijk (1 min.), Jordaan (2 min.), several cosy streetmarkets (4 min.), Nine Streets or Negen Straatjes (5 min.), Anne Frank House (6 min.), Amsterdam Central Station (7 min.), Dam Square (10 min.), concerthall Muziekgebouw aan het IJ (25 min.), Eye Filmmuseum (30 min.).

In the apartment you will find several books about the history of Amsterdam, some tourist guides and also our Folder with a lot more information about restaurants, shops and cult
host_about:
We are Maarten & Lisa, father and daughter. In September 2014 we started Canal View Amsterdam in one of the apartments on the Brouwersgracht. Lisa grew up at Brouwersgracht 49 and Maarten is still living there.

Lisa is working as a psychologist with children and adolescents and as a university teacher. She is now living in another neighborhood of Amsterdam, but always finds it nice to come back at the Brouwersgracht. That really feels like coming home.

Maarten is working since 2010 as an independent visual artist. He had previous careers in Baroque music as a double base player, and in child psychology. 

We really hope that you will feel at home at the Brouwersgracht as much as we do!

neighborhood_overview: In terms of design and development, De Baarsjes is like Oud West: densely populated with few green spaces, but lots of wide streets, squares and facilities. In the 1990s, many neglected buildings were refurbished or replaced by new construction. Mercatorplein was extensively renovated and is the only square completely designed by Berlage that still exists in Amsterdam, thanks to a campaign by residents, which ensured that nothing was demolished. Oud West was a higher priority than De Baarsjes in terms of redevelopment, so De Baarsjes is still lagging in social development by comparison. Even so, it remains a popular neighbourhood with many satisfied residents.

Superclean space

The space

neighborhood_overview:
Our house is right on the edge of the city centre, in the OOSTERPARK area, with it's own vibe and sparkle.
We are close to the zoo (Artis) and just around the corner you find the Oosterpark, the Tropen Museum, relaxed bars (Javastreet area) good food and the famous Windmill Brewery 't IJ.
The Dapper market is our daily market for fresh vegetables, cheese, fish and bread, and also fabric and clothes. Every day between 10-16, not on Sundays.
Several supermarkets around the corner, on the First van Swindenstraat (open from 8-22) and a night shop on Linnaeusstraat (open until 01:00).
host_about:
Once I stayed in a tiny room in the heart of Tribeca, NYC. Outside the window, squashed between brick walls stood a tall tree "planted by Yoko Ono". A memorable sales pitch for a queen-size bed on top of the world. Living on Wooster Street I was a local for a week, a fantastic experience. I would love to offer this kind of experience to my guests when staying in Amsterdam.
The house is mainly occupied by me, my son and Bonnie the cat, but we love to entertain friends and family with food and stories, so the house can be quiet as well as very lively. A family home in short ;-)
Our room for rent is on the second floor of a 4 story house, and with it's own bathroom on the same floor, it is all rather private and relaxed, for the guests as well as us. We live on the two top floors, just a shout away if any help is needed. 
My personal interests are art, photography, film and design, and I love to show my guests the local hotspots. New shows and exhibitions, exciting places to go for shopping, coffee or food, I am happy to share if you want to know. 
I travelled west as far as San Francisco and east as far as Varanasi. Both ways there was always a 'friend's connection' to help out with local stuff. This was before Airbnb existed, and now through this organization I can maybe be that connection for you. Happy to help.
In daily life I am art director, photographer and blogger.

host_about:
Hi! I'm Jacqueline, 35, live and work in Amsterdam as a nurse. 
Love to travel, see and explore another world, cultures and habits. 
I try to make a long trip every year, or at least a few short trips. The most memorable trip was the one to Cameroon. But i am also a huge fan of Asia. Next on the list is South America.
Next to traveling i like to cook, wander around, take photo's, catching a good film, host or attend dinnerparty's. 

What i love about airbnb is the experience of seeing and feeling the city/village as a local. Therefore i'd like to give fellowtravelers something back. 
Because my travels are often for a longer period of time and therefore i am not allways at home to welcome guests personally (unfortunately), i asked 'the friendly host' to take over when i am away. I have good experiences with them and i trust them to make the stay just as personal as i would do so myself.

neighborhood_overview:

Onze buurt (de Bijlmermeer) grenst aan een groot park met de Gaasperplas, een meer waar je kunt zwemmen en zeilen. Ons huis is de perfecte uitvalsbasis om Amsterdam, Utrecht, andere Nederlandse steden en de natuurgebieden rond Amsterdam te bezoeken. Er is een treinstation en metrostation vlakbij (10 minuten lopen)
De Bijlmermeer is in de jaren 70 gebouwd als "stad van de toekomst" met hoge flats, met relatief ruime appartementen en veel gras, planten, borders en bomen. In de jaren 80 en 90 raakte het gebied in verval, maar sinds de eeuwwisseling floreert Amsterdam Zuid-Oost, met 144 nationaliteiten, een grote bioscoop, het Ajax-stadion en grote en kleine bedrijven. We wonen hier met veel plezier!

host_about: We zijn samen sinds 2001 en trouwden in 2002. We houden zowel van de stad als van groen. The building is rightfully part of the historic city centre in Amsterdam, being more than a 100 years old, built in iconic Amsterdam style. The house is authentically built with beautiful stained glass and wooden floors. The house has narrow and steep stairs, which is also very typical for authentic Amsterdam houses.

neighborhood_overview:
Discover the beautiful and abundant city of Amsterdam from the heart of its historic city centre right in-between the Central Station and the oldest part of the city, Jordaan. Right behind the house you will find Amsterdam’s famous canals and all it’s other main attractions closeby. The street offers many different food & drink options and even plenty of shops to get great souvenirs. At the end of the street there is an organic food market on Wednesdays (Haarlemmerplein), and on Mondays & Saturdays around the corner at the ‘Noordermarkt’. At the end of the street you will start walking into the commercial shopping area of the city where you will find all major stores and brands.
The ‘Jordaan’ is famous for the 9 Little Streets (9 Straatjes), filled with local boutiques, the Anne Frank house, and local brown cafes. neighborhood_overview: De Helmersbuurt staat bekend om een rustige, mooie buurt. Dichtbij het vondelpark, Oud-Zuid, Oud-West en centrum. Ideaal voor stellen, families, vrienden (groepen).
host_about:
Als meisje opgegroeid in het zuiden van Nederland (Limburg) was het altijd een droom om naar de grote stad te verhuizen. In 2010 was het zover. Na het huren van een eerste appartementje midden op de Wallen (Amsterdam Centrum) en de stad verder leren verkennen, vond ik ruim een jaar later ons huidige appartement in Amsterdam Oud-West. Een van de meest populaire buurten onder de Amsterdammers. Met veel plezier heb ik met andere studenten, waaronder vriendinnen, hier gewoond. Sinds 2019 woon ik samen met mijn vriend.
Sfeer, gezelligheid en warme kleuren voeren de boventoon in ons ruime appartement. Het interieur wisselend uit ikea, new design en vintage treasures zijn met veel liefde uitgezocht. De ruime eet- en woonkamer geeft je, na een lange dag door de Amsterdamse straten, het gevoel van thuiskomen. De identieke slaapkamers geven een ultiem gevoel van hotelkwaliteit. De badkamer is voorzien van toiletartikelen en uitgerust met een douche en ligbad. Samen met de luchtzuiverende planten kunt u helemaal tot rust komen. 
Voor de thuischef is de keuken van alle gemakken voorzien. Vanwege de middag- en avondzon kunt u zowel voor als achter op het ruime balkon dineren. 
Bedankt dat u de tijd heeft genomen om ons beter te leren kennen en wij hopen u snel te mogen ontvangen. U bent meer dan van harte welkom!
Liefs, Sophie & Emre

host_about:
My name is Laila,

Born and raised in Amsterdam,  traveling the States for work for the last couple of years.

This lovely low- maintenance city is a metropole within a village; it combines the thrill and diversity of serious metropoles with the cosy and safe qualities of a village. It's the kind of city of love and it's the kind of person I am; I love the thrill and the quiet. 

I have always been fascinated by storytelling and political campaigning and managed to make a living out of that fascination. I used to work in political campaigning but switched to journalism in 2016. As a free lancer, I travel the United States a lot and touch base in Amsterdam about 6 months a year. 

Furthermore I love cinema, basketball, cooking, dining, wine, springtime and long walks. With the ones I love, of course. In 2016, I started surfing and have taken every chance ever since to catch waves.  

I started booking with airbnb in 2011  and knowing the joy of staying in a great and homy place  decided to be part of the sharing economy all the way and share my place and knowledge of this city with like minded travelers around the world in 2014. I really do believe the sharing experience adds to the any stay, anywhere. My home is not a holiday rental - I care to share it with travelers who enjoy the sharing and local kind of travel and treat a home that same way.

description:
We love to welcome you in our spacious loft/apartment in the CENTRE of Amsterdam. Possible to PARK (a regular size) car FOR FREE, safe inside and save €90/ day on parkingfees. Ask the owners!

The loft has a private entrance, bathroom and pantry. Free welcome drinks, coffee/ tea & toiletpaper. Often late check out possible.

All the highlights (zoo, museums) within walking distance. Just around the corner are nice restaurants, bars and supermarkets!

Notice: NON SMOKING.

The space
The loft is 95m2 with high ceilings of 4 meter and there is a typical brick wall. It is a unique space, very cosy. There ia one large bedroom and two double beds. Look at the pictures to get a good idea.

The loft comes with free parking indoors (cars normal size); saves on the Amsterdam parking fees E90/ day. Open the big garagedoors and you have a nice terrace to sit in the sun...!

The loft is used for AirBnB purposes only.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartement/ loft is in the centre of Amsterdam, situated in a quiet street. Just around the corner is the zoo Artis, Amstel/ Skinny Bridge and the Hermitage museum. Also nice restaurants, coffeecorners and supermarkets. A small SPAR is within 200 meters. Bigger supermarkets within 500 meters...
Dam square and Rijksmuseum/ Van Gogh museum are within walking distance (15-20 minutes). Anne Frank House 20-30 minutes.
It is possible to swim in some canals when it is hot. Within 5 minutes there is a swimming area on the Entrepot dok.
The apartment/loft is on the ground floor and has big garage doors. When open it is a nice place to sit in the sun and enjoy a drink!
host_about:
With my three kids and three cats I live above the apartment. I work at a public houding agency and I am a painter. My paintings are in  the apartment and also on my website (Website hidden by Airbnb) 

I am living in Amsterdam since 1986. I love the Amsterdam because it is a vibrant city with lots of restaurants and museums. I love the canals and the beautiful houses. And you only need a bike to go places.

neighborhood_overview:
One of the oldest neighborhoods in Amsterdam, and centrally located for the Dam Square, Anne Frank House, Noorder Market and the VondelPark. Known as the artists district, you’ll find galleries within an easy throw of an paintbrush. Cool shops, all sorts of restaurants and grocery shopping are within a few minutes walk.

The Canal the house is sited on has a rich history of art and industry, and is one of the prettiest and most instagrammed locations in the city.
host_about:
We live on a beautiful canal in the heart of Amsterdam, and have been here for 14 years. Adam is English, Camilla is Danish/Dutch mix. We have 3 languages at home! We run a growing software business in the city (CustomerGauge). We have 2 kids living with us and 2 older kids at college. We love travelling and exploring. We gave up our cars in Amsterdam (no parking) and cycle everywhere, including commuting to work and dropping kids off at school.

In the past we have booked quality accommodation with Airbnb in Amsterdam, and it's worked out well for our business guests up to 30 days. We have also had great experiences booking on our own trips in USA and UK for family vacations. 

We are delighted to welcome people from all walks of life to  our house for short family stays.. We hope you love it as much as we do. 

 In both our professional and private lives we embrace diversity. We look forward to making new friends as hosts and guests.

The space

In room 2 is the bedroom with a wonderfully large box spring (180X200 cm), with flat screen TV (which has a chrome cabinet so you can stream everything via your smartphone), private shower and gives you access to the large floating private terrace with lounge sofa. host_about:
I am a realtor since 20 years. Some of my hobbies are travelling,  Ibiza, (race) cycling, my work, cars, soccer and my close friends and family. 

We started this company 20 years ago. In April 2013 we started with renting out through Airbnb. With our experience in letting out to expats from the biggest Multinationals (Shell/Unilever/Johnson&Johnson) we know what people expect in a temporary apartment. 

We try to develop our apartments in a tasteful neutral style with high quality finishing and - furniture on nice locations like the Amsterdam Jordaan Area. Our apartments are not on the busiest places of Amsterdam but always on a maximum 3 minute walk from the canals. 

All our (Amsterdam)apartments are fully licensed by town hall what means that safety is on place 1. Infrared smoke detectors, flight plans, not too many people in 1 flat, no drugs etc.

We try to offer a hotel idea but than in an apartment. So more privacy, luxury, convenience and space on a AAA location but for a better price!

A definite no go is asking for a discount. If our prices are too high I would suggest to rent a bed where the owner was in the night before. 

Also we dont accept guests without any reviews. No exceptions. Sorry.


What is also convenient in our opinion is that we do not live our selves in the apartments. So You dont  sleep on a bed where someone has slept on for 5 years already. 

After every guest the apartments are professionally cleaned and so are  the towels and bedlinen by a professional company.

please see our reviews for confirmation if you are not convinced yet!

neighborhood_overview: Stylish and modern, the Amsterdam Prince Island by YAYS is beautifully located in an exclusive area. The Western Isles are a living museum, once home to ship works and the West India Trading Company's warehouses, which buzzed with activity in the early 17th century. Nowadays the district is a world unto itself, cut through with historical canals and linked with small drawbridges.

YAYS Group is an established serviced apartment provider managing 15 aparthotels in Amsterdam, The Hague, the Paris metropolitan area, and Antwerp under the lifestyle brands YAYS (fully serviced aparthotels) and by YAYS (serviced apartments with partially self-serviced solutions). 
Each of the 500 YAYS Group apartments is stylish, spacious, fully equipped, and located in a convenient area. A turn-key living space ready for comfortable short to long stays for leisure and business guests alike, and a base for urban exploration made easier by the YAYS Insiders. With outstanding local knowledge and a talent for sharing it, the YAYS Insiders are more than ordinary hotel staff. A YAYS Group serviced apartment is a home away from home that sets you on the inside track to local living.

The district is roughly located between the Amstel in the west, the Weespertrekvaart in the east, the Amstel station in the north and the border between Duivendrecht and Amsterdam-Zuidoost in the south. The Duivendrechtsevaart offers a connection for shipping.

The business park, which was developed in the early 1960s, offers space for all kinds of companies and non-heavy industry. The former Bijlmerbajes and the basic rail workplace with an open-air parking facility for GVB buses are located in the district. At the end of the eighties, the Omval was redeveloped, in which besides three office towers also luxury apartments appeared, with which Overamstel had also become a residential area.

neighborhood_overview:
Amsterdam West is one of the most buzzing & diverse neighborhoods. You find almost everything there! It's an area with a laid back attitude an home to a cool mix of small stores and many restaurant hotspots. A great diversity of hipster- proof coffee places (to drink coffee, not the type that sells pot ;)), cool concept stores and bars with outside terraces. Amsterdam West is also great for foodies! You find a variety of kitchens and ambiences that will serve every needs.

Furthermore within walking distance you reach the 17th century city centre, while you walk by the cool bars and restaurants before you know it you entered the Jordaan district. Here are the famous UNESCO listed canals like Herengracht, Prinsengracht and Keizersgracht. We are proud to say that our own area has recently been nominated for an UNESCO listing as well, since the archtecture is from a stream of the international Expressionist architecture.

neighborhood_overview:
Amsterdam's Jordaan is probably the most famous neighbourhood in the Netherlands.
The Jordaan is nothing but highlights. Maze-like streets offer hidden courtyards, cafés (traditional but also trendy), art galleries and pleasantly noisy neighbours. One also has access to some of the more scenic outdoor markets in the country. In particular, Noordermarkt has a flea market on Monday mornings and an organic farmers' market on Saturdays. There are many more modern, trendy bars around Noordermarkt and along Westerstraat and Rozengracht. The side-streets that run south of Westerstraat have recently developed into a strong culinary district with some of the city’s more highly regarded restaurants.

description:
Compact and comfortable one-bedroom apartment with garden, for up to four guests, in the trendy West area of Amsterdam.

The space
This comfortable accommodation, wooden floors and large windows that allow plenty of natural light, is perfect for two couples or a family. The bright and cheerful living area has a large sofa (converts into a double bed), and a flat screen television with cable. The separate kitchen is well equipped, includes a stove, coffee machine (coffee, sugar and tea), oven, microwave, fridge and freezer.

There is also a dining table for four. The bedroom has a comfortable double bed. The bathroom is modern and features a toilet, washbasin and shower. The bonus of the apartment is the garden, where you can enjoy a morning cup of coffee or evening glass of wine.

neighborhood_overview:
Ons huis ligt in Tuindorp Oostzaan, een oer-Hollandse wijk gebouwd in de jaren dertig voor de scheepswerf arbeiders.
Het ligt vlakbij de NDSM werf, een oud haventerrein met industrieel uiterlijk die volop in gebruik is als culturele broedplaats.
Liefhebbers voor cultuur, horeca, festivals en vlooienmarkten kunnen hier hun hart ophalen.
Zo is er maandelijkse de grootste vlooienmarkt van Europa (IJhallen), zijn er diverse horeca gelegenheden zoals Pllek, Noorderlicht, IJkantine, Loetje, de Pannenkoekenboot en meer.
De andere kant op, op 10 minuten fietsafstand bevind zich het natuurgebied 't Twiske waar de natuur liefhebber zijn hart kan ophalen. Ook is er veel te beleven voor kinderen met een biologisch dynamische boerderij, avonturenspeelplaats, zwemgelegenheid in natuurwater, kanoën en meer.
Op loopafstand is Noordoogst, een bruisende groene plek rondom de duurzame voedselketen met lokale ondernemers en horeca. Hier is tevens een natuurspeeltuin.

neighborhood_overview: Traditionally a blue collar neighbourhood just a stone's throw away from the heart of town, 'De Baarsjes', is what one calls 'on the rise'. All around us we see new initiatives popping up; from intimate coffee bars and restaurants, to cool boutiques with local designers. Please ask the staff for inside info on where to go!
host_about:
Hotel Not Hotel is a place in Amsterdam where a room isn’t just a room, but a work of art with its own creator, story, and identity. Most of them designed and specially made by Collaboration-O, a group of young designers that originated from the Eindhoven Design Academy, and one by Arno Coenen and his partner IRIS.

When you wake up, you step into an art-filled, exhibition-like space instead of an anonymous lobby or hallway. The entire hotel is one big living room, with cosy seating areas between the cottages. Combined with our luxury beds and other facilities, Hotel Not Hotel offers an unrivalled experience. 
Besides all this, we feel that the value of a city lies in experiencing its local day-to-day life. As we are closely connected to Amsterdam and its numerous creative entrepreneurs, we know where to send you for a night on the town, a hidden culinary gem, or an upcoming artist’s exhibition. 

The bar connected to Hotel Not Hotel is called Kevin Bacon. Just like the actor, the bar has zero pretention, it always delivers, and it makes sure everybody has a good time.

Kevin Bacon is not your typical hotel bar. It’s where locals get their morning coffee or a quick breakfast. It’s where friends meet for a cocktail or a beer before diving into the nightlife, and where hotel guests let their hair down after a long day in the city.

When the weather is good, the ‘Whitey the White’ terrace is sunny like a perfectly fried egg. The staff’s friendly attitude shines all year round.

description:
Are you looking for a very special stay on a beautiful houseboat in Amsterdam? Don't look any further, you already found the perfect spot!

The space
This incredible houseboat is situated at one of the best spots of Amsterdam. There's no houseboat in Amsterdam like ours where you can wake up with a panoramic 360 view over the historic harbour.
If you want to stay at a really special and gorgeous place in Amsterdam you don't have to look any further. This is your chance to experience a unique stay on a typical dutch houseboat.

You will sleep on the 1st floor and will have your own personal entrance and facilities, like the bathroom and fridge and a huge private terrace where you’ll have the best views to see amazing sunsets.

We can place a babybed when you're travelling with a child.
Breakfast is not included, in walking distance you can find the best spots to enjoy an amazing breakfast and there is a little fridge stocked with dri
neighborhood_overview: The neighbourhood is something special: in the big city but still a close community. You’ll easy access to public transport, City centre, Jordaan area and Central Station: it is all on walking distance.
host_about:
Eltjo works has his own company with cbd-products and Liselore en is setting up a bussiness with handmade clothes and accessories from Bali. We have 3 boys, in the age of 8,6 and the little one is 2 years old.

In 2013 we bought the boat " The Calidris". The main reason to live on a boat was to stay in the city, but still had enough space and above all, freedom. It feels like a little community in this street, because the boat people hang out together, help eachother and know eachother well.

We are very happy to live in such a special place in Amsterdam, enough space, nice views, but still connected to the city! We like cooking together, traveling with our 3 boys, designing our home or making trips with our camper.

In 2014 we started our B&B. Where you sleep now, it used to be the captain's cabin. We immediately removed the stairs, so we do not miss the space at all. It as always a dream for me to run a little boutique hotel. Nowadays we don't run a hotel, but a pittoresque B&B, which we really enjoy. It is fun to meet people all over the world who mostly have a great time at our boat. When you would like to see how houseboat-people live just knock on the door and we will show you around!

Enjoy your stay!


Eltjo

The space

neighborhood_overview:
The WG area/Old West area (or Helmersbuurt) is a truly unique neighborhood in the city center of amsterdam. It is safe, low on traffic, quiet with lots of kids facilities, shops and restaurants, markets etc, all within minutes walking distance. The vondelpark is literally around the corner, for a morning workout or an easy stroll through the park. The park has a free kiddypool in te summer and is a good entrance to the city center.

We moved to this lovely corner penthouse because the great facilities for kids, the Vondelpark and all the shops and restaurants within minutes walking distance. It is in the city center however quiet and safe for the kids. The playground in front of the house not only has a playground for the smallest but also a soccer cage, ping-pong table and has 2 patengue fields.
host_about:
We are a family of 5 (3 kids, two girls of 16 and 14 and one son of 12) and have been living in this neighbourhood (centre/oud west/westerpark area) since 1995. Marc is an MD and Brenda a graphic designer, we like to travel, go to the theater and concerts. Bike around the city and enjoy the atmosphere. 

What we really like about the house is the nice quiet and relaxing view over the canal. The area we live in is a great and vibrant area, with a lot of restaurants, coffeecorners, venues and bars within walking distance. It's very close to all the amsterdam highlights (10 minutes to Anne Frank house for instance), but on a quit canal. 
We enjoy the interactions with different people and cultures and like them to feel at home in our hometown.

name: Unique ground floor appt. in the centre
description:
Spacious apartment on the ground floor, with a private garden, of a 18th century canal house centrally located in between the historical Heren and Keizers Gracht. Located in the very hart of Amsterdam, near Damsquare.

The space
The 18th century canal house centrally located in between the historical Heren and Keizer Gracht. It is a five minute walk to the Jordaan district of Amsterdam; an area full of small restaurants, cafes, galleries and historic attractions such as the Anne Frank Museum.
The apartment is spacious and an ideal place to stay for couples. It has a very quiet bedroom with comfortable double bed.

For the duration of your stay you will be provided with clean towels and linen, and also have access to the free Wifi

Guest access
You will have access to the whole apartment on the ground floor including bathroom with a bath, toilet and shower. There is an open kitchen and cosy living room with a fire place.
neighborhood_overview:
Relative to key Amsterdam attractions the apartment is very centrally located and not too far from anything! A few minutes of walking can get you to the Anne Frank House, the Royal Palace, the Dam Square, the ‘9 streets’ for great restaurants and shopping, the famous Prinsengracht canal, and much more. On Saturdays the Noordermarkt hosts a local Farmer’s market and on Mondays a Flea Market, and is only a few blocks away as well.

If you decide to rent a bicycle then within a 10-minute cycle you can access the Museumplein where the famous Van Gogh Museum and Rijksmuseum are located. Cycling is one of the best ways to explore the city and enjoy the canals- there are several places you can rent from near to the apartment.

neighborhood_overview: It’s just a 15 minute walk from Central Station but a whole world away from the hustle and bustle of the vibrant city centre. The market is 2 min walk from the house and on from Mon-Sat. Public transport and all sorts of handy shops are 3 min away in the parallel Kinkerstraat.
The area has dozens of bars/cafes, restaurants, shops, etc. You can walk 5 min to the central canal ring.

neighborhood_overview:
Oud West is in the heart of the city and close to both Vondelpark and Rembrandtpark. Ten Katestraat market is an excellent outdoor market with its charming cross-street Bellamystraat giving the area an old-fashion village vibe – complete with dance studio and blacksmith. It’s criss-crossed with commercial streets, including Overtoom which has become a major interiors boulevard. And to attest to the area’s child-friendliness, the Bosboom Toussaintstraat with its many children-oriented stores is referred to as ‘Amsterdam’s delivery room’.

Boasting 178 nationalities, Oud West is multicultural but is pretty much free of the stereotypes that come with that.

Eating, drinking, etc

description:
Welcome to our bright & spacious apartment on the two top floors of a typical Amsterdam building in a very nice area close to the Vondelpark. We are sure you will love it because it's large, bright, tastefully decorated, with a fully equipped open plan kitchen and a roof terrace. Located in the popular neighbourhood of Oud West, in the heart of the city and close to the Vondelpark, Jordaan and the canals. Welcome!

The space
Bright and spacious apartment on the top two floors, perfectly located in 'Oud-West', whithin 5 minutes walking distance to the Vondelpark and close to the city centre. Perfect for couples, business travelers, families and a small group of friends.

The apartment has a total of 110 m2, a balcony and roof terrace. It has central heating and wifi.

The 1st floor of the apartment is an open space with a fully equiped open kitchen, large dining table and doors to the balcony. On the street side there is a comfortable living wi
neighborhood_overview:
Our apartment is located in a quiet street, yet lively and popular neighborhood with many shops, cafes and cozy restaurants.

The neighbourhood has a great mix of culture and economic levels. It's a melting pot with lots of students, young creative people as well as families with (small) children.

The area is within walking distance of the Vondelpark, Amsterdam's most popular park. It's near the museum disctrict with the Rijksmuseum, the Van Gogh musem and the Stedelijk museum. And it's within 10 minutes of the city centers beautiful canals.
host_about: I work at the municipality of Amsterdam as a continuous improvement manager. Together with my partner, I also have a small company dedicated to champagne and wine tastings. We both love travelling and discovering new places as well as returning to beautiful countries such as Marocco where I lived as an expat child, Vietnam where my brother lives and la douce France where we love to go camping with our 10 years old son.

name: Amsterdam Farm Lodge: quircky, old farmers style
description:
Enjoy a very special green setting on the edges of Amsterdam. A sustainable place to stay, to play and to relax. Not too far from the city, yet tranquille and lots off space.

If you come for a drugs vacation, please find another place to stay. This place is not suited for that, we don't allow the use of marihuana at our premesis.

Please read our COVID-19 measures in the description underneath.

The space
Spacious ground floor apartment especially suited for families, in a child friendly environment. The 'Amsterdam Farm Lodge' is located on the terrain of the urban farming project 'NoordOogst', a very special place on the edge of Amsterdam, just a few steps away from the hustling and bustling NDSM wharf. But also a lot to see and do on site. Sustainability is important to us, therefore we made use of recycled materials to decorate the place.

The apartment has 2 bedrooms, a living, a dining room, toilet, bathroom en well equipped kit
neighborhood_overview:
We are on the site of an awesome urban farming project, you'll find fields with crops, pigs, chickens, a restaurant, a veggie take-away, kids daycare, natural play ground, woodworking, natural playground, a beekeeper, a wine yard and a brewery. And plenty of space to play.

The hustling and bustling NDSM wharf with is only 15 minutes away by bike, from here the ferry to Central Station departs. Ten minutes biking to the other side you can find nature area 'het Twiske' where you can swim, bike and hike. Only 10 minutes by foot you can discover the hidden nature area of 'Noorder IJplas'. The Zaanse Schans, IJselmeer, beach and 'bollenstreek' are easy to reach.
host_about: We are a couple from Amsterdam and we love to travel. A few years ago we've hosted a wintersport chalet in Austria. We liked it so much that we wanted to open our own B&B. What started out with the idea of a small cabin in the backyard, became much bigger when we got the opportunity of opening the Amsterdam Farm Lodge at the urban farming project of NoordOogst. The Amsterdam Farm Lodge is a project for 10 years and it consists of 7 holiday apartments. Let the adventure begin....

Oud-West is loaded with lovely fashion and homedesign boutiques, bakeries, coffee shops (both for actual coffee and the other ones) and trendy bars & restaurants. name: Amazing and bright private studio on houseboat
description:
Welcome aboard!

We've transformed part of our houseboat into a luxury design apartment. Come for a unique houseboat stay with your own convenient key safe entrance, spacious, yet cosy living room, a queen size bed, en suite walk-in rain shower, separate toilet, and a kitchenette for making coffee, tea or heating up a light meal.
On the front deck you can enjoy our beautiful harbour and Dutch skies, and if you fancy you can even jump off our boat for a swim, we often do :-)

The space
We live in the Oude Houthaven (old wood harbour) together with 30 something other houseboats.
The harbour is beautiful, and perfectly located: close enough to easily walk (or bike) into town, yet in a calm and residential neighbourhood. You are surrounded by old warehouses and spectacular modern architecture like the new landmark ‘Pontsteiger’. There’s several bars and restaurants close by, as well as supermarkets within a 10 minute walk.
The famous area Jo
neighborhood_overview:
The Oude Houthaven is a friendly little 'village' - a quiet oasis in the heart of a chaotic city. Our neighbours, like us, are all families with kids. In summer, the water turns into a giant swimming pool, so don't forget your swimming gear!
Our boat is surrounded by water. Our kids are fine and happy growing up here, but we cannot take any responsibility for other people's kids.
Please respect our neighbours. Therefore: no parties, no extra visitors and no weed smoking please. Upon making a booking you are agreeing to these rules.
host_about:
We are a family of 4 plus our lovely Siberian cat called Boris. We have two teenage girls. Jeremy is a boat builder and has transformed many houseboats in Amsterdam over the years. We bought ship Houtman in 2010 in quite a state, and are slowly but surely transforming it.
Houtman has been a houseboat in de Houthaven area since the mid eighties. In her previous life Houtman sailed the European inland waters transporting all sorts of bulk goods.

neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located in the middle of the ''De Pijp'' neighborhood. De Pijp is a hip and happening neighbourhood with a large concentration of restaurants, cafés and bars catering to just about every class and taste.

A few places in Amsterdam have undergone the transformation that de Pijp has gone through in the last 20 years. Once considered a claustrophobic workers neighbourhood with small leaky houses, it’s now home to a multitude of creatives, young families and start ups. It's absolutely exploding with the internationally oriented bars and restaurants to cater to them all with the Albert Cuyp (a seemingly never-ending street market) as the beating heart of it all.

The area is intersected by the Ceintuurbaan, leaving its northern half with the charming Sarphatipark and the southern part with its special Japanese shops and restaurants.

The nearest airport (Schiphol) is about 16 KM from the apartment.

neighborhood_overview: The lively nightspot and market square Nieuwmarkt, found in the old city centre just east of the Red Light District, has been a centre for commerce and socialising in Amsterdam since the 17th century. Created by filling in the surrounding canals, the square's location just inside the old city gate made it a popular spot for traders and shoppers looking for fresh produce. Today, Nieuwmarkt still holds a daily market as well as an organic fare market on Saturdays, but arguably its biggest draw is the amount of cafés, restaurants and coffeeshops that surround it, making this square a perfect place to spend a sunny day sitting on a terrace. The Nieuwmarkt metro stop can be found on the square, which caused quite a bit of protest during its construction but now serves as one of the city's most central and most used stops on the metro service.

neighborhood_overview:
The house can be found on Realeneiland, a small island that is part of the city centre of Amsterdam, but slightly hidden away from the rest. The realeneiland is part of a group of three islands that together are called 'The Western Isles' (Westelijke eilanden), the two other isles being Bickerseiland and Prinseneiland.

The Western Isles are among the oldest areas of Amsterdam and have a rich history. The house itself is actually one of the fourteen original 'captain's houses' (kapiteinswoningen) of Realeneiland.

The house carries the name 'In 't Anker', which translates as 'in the anchor'; the name along with the house's symbol can be seen on the gable. It can be found on the Zandhoek - the name for the street and corner of the island. As you walk around the neighbourhood you will see boats everywhere, as the island also functions as a small city harbour.

host_about:
H401 is the name of a 17th century canal house in the very centre of Amsterdam at one of the most beautiful canal conjunctions. The house has a stunning history as a hiding place during WWII, but other than the Anne Frank house the building is still used for living and working . In their gallery and studio space H401 features a unique high end cultural programme based on the history of the house that has always been a magnet for artists, writers and people on the move. Castrum Peregrini was the code name during the war and literally translates as 'castle of the pilgrim'. The original hiding place is still preserved and the various floors and spaces represent the houses vibrant history since the 1940s.

We are three friends, Michael, Frans and Lars that run H401 today and we also live in the building, which is big enough to be a universe in itself. We offer three luxurious independent guest appartments, both recently restored in a minimalist manner, with a stunning view to the canal in the front  facing a row of historic 17th century gables and the monumental Krijtberg Church in the back. The rooms offer the unique experience of a historic place with contemprary comfort (state of the art beds, linen, towels etc) The appartments offer equiped kitchens and coffee, tea, and some simple breakfast incredients. Though the accomodations are situated at a quite part of the famous 'gouden bocht' of the Herengracht, the lively and fashionable nine streets are just a stone's throw away; they offer stylish cafes, bars, shops, lunch and diner possibilities. All famous sites and musea are walking distance. Amsterdam at its very best!

host_about:
I am a realtor since 20 years. Some of my hobbies are travelling,  Ibiza, (race) cycling, my work, cars, soccer and my close friends and family. 

We started this company 20 years ago. In April 2013 we started with renting out through Airbnb. With our experience in letting out to expats from the biggest Multinationals (Shell/Unilever/Johnson&Johnson) we know what people expect in a temporary apartment. 

We try to develop our apartments in a tasteful neutral style with high quality finishing and - furniture on nice locations like the Amsterdam Jordaan Area. Our apartments are not on the busiest places of Amsterdam but always on a maximum 3 minute walk from the canals. 

All our (Amsterdam)apartments are fully licensed by town hall what means that safety is on place 1. Infrared smoke detectors, flight plans, not too many people in 1 flat, no drugs etc.

We try to offer a hotel idea but than in an apartment. So more privacy, luxury, convenience and space on a AAA location but for a better price!

A definite no go is asking for a discount. If our prices are too high I would suggest to rent a bed where the owner was in the night before. 

Also we dont accept guests without any reviews. No exceptions. Sorry.


What is also convenient in our opinion is that we do not live our selves in the apartments. So You dont  sleep on a bed where someone has slept on for 5 years already. 

After every guest the apartments are professionally cleaned and so are  the towels and bedlinen by a professional company.

please see our reviews for confirmation if you are not convinced yet!

The apartment is within walking distance of the Albert Cuyp market, the Sarphatipark, and the Amstel river. I recently bought the apartment and couldn't be happier with it, so I am very excited to make you fall in love with the place and the neighborhood as well!

The space

neighborhood_overview:
The Pijp is one of the nicest and most trendy areas of Amsterdam, with tons of great restaurants, squares, shops and botiques. The popular Albert Cuyp Market and Sarphatipark are just around the corner. Due to its central location, all the other areas of Amsterdam can be easily reached by bike or public transport. There are a lot of bike rental places at walking distance. Just around the corner of the apartment there is a lovely large playing ground with ping pong tables, picnic tables, and lots of playground equipment, which makes it the perfect place to stay with kids.

The apartment is located in a beautiful location in the heart of De Pijp. The street itself is designed by M. de Klerk and P .L. Kramer, the most important architects of the Amsterdamse School. There is a visitors center at the end of the street which provides tours around the neighborhood in case you want to learn more about the history and iconic architecture!

As a tenant I cared for other peoples' goods. I even often repaired broken things in the houses where I lived. I am moved and inspired by world leaders who make a difference in improving the world. I try to contribute to this by my jobs and am dedicated to empower those who have less access to basic goods like water of education.


Ik geniet van Amsterdam, maar houd ook erg van reizen. Door reizen heb ik geleerd hoe leuk het is als anderen hun huis openstellen. Ik ben gek op film en buiten festivals. Daar hebben we er genoeg van in Amsterdam. Tijdens mijn jarenlange wonen in landen in Afrika, Midden Oosten, Zuid Amerika en New York heb ik als huurder vaak kapotte dingen gerepareerd. Ik ben sociaal bewogen en kom op voor de zwakkere buur in de wereld.

Groet, Lisette

neighborhood_overview:
Oud-West and in particular De Baarsjes is an upcoming area close to everything the beautiful city of Amsterdam has to offer. It is a 5 minute walk towards the public transport (tram) which takes you within another max of 15 minutes to wherever you wanna go within the city.
If you wanna walk the nearby area you will find both the Vondelpark, as the bustling Kinkerstraat, Jan Pieter Heijestraat & Overtoom within a 5 to 10 minute range.
If you want to feel like a true Amsterdammian or 'Mokummer' as we would say, we would suggest you to rent a pushbike and cruise the city like the rest of us do. neighborhood_overview:
You will be staying in the heart of the historical center of Amsterdam, near the Singel on the Canal Belt. You will find many (traditional) bars, cafes, coffeeshops, restaurants and shops on your door step. Within minutes you are on Dam Square (where the Royal Palace and the New Church are located), at the Anne Frank Museum or Amsterdam Museum, at the flower market, in the famous 'Jordaan' area, at the 'Nine Streets' shopping area, in the Haarlemmerstraat, Chinatown, or red light district. neighborhood_overview:
Living on the water gives you a sense of relaxation. Everyday feels like a holiday living here. We swim every day right out of our living room. Also the sunlight bounced by the water gives amazing reflections on the walls and ceiling. At night you can see the beautiful lights of the city centre just sitting on the couch.
Although really close to the city center our street is nice and peaceful. Not to much traffic or tourist around, the kids can play outside under supervision. Right in front of the boat is a little foot and bike bridge which leads to a wonderful park, where you can lay down in de grass or enjoy a good coffee/breakfast/lunch/dinner at Pension Homeland. Or enjoy a beautiful meal at restaurant 'De Scheepskameel'. Only a two minute walk but very popular with locals so a reservation is a must. neighborhood_overview:
Vondelbuurt

Once you cross the Overtoom you’ll be in the Vondelbuurt, the beautiful, leafy area surrounding the Vondelpark, so named after the playwright Vondel (a sort of Dutch Shakespeare). Points of interest around here include the Hollandse Manege (a riding school hidden away between the façades of upperclass family homes), the Vondelkerk (a circular church in the style of a gothic cathedral), the Vondelpark Open Air Theatre (in summer) and the park itself is always a good place to sit on a sunny day. (Good to know: the Vondelpark was originally built as a recreational area for cyclists so do watch out for the bikes!)

Close to: Stedelijk Museum, Van Gough Museum, Rijksmuseum, MoCo Museum, Food Hallen and the Vondelpark.

name: Idyllic, peaceful house + garden in trendy area!
description:
In a pittoresk calm street in Amsterdam North we (me, husband + toddler) own a pretty cozy house with a green front & back garden. No city noises & exhaust fumes but singing birds & the smell of flowers. The city center is within 20 mins reach by bike & free ferry. Free parking! Ideal stay for a couple or young family. Our house and all appliances are for your use, including the garden. Closeby are the Zaanse Schans, Volendam, Twiske. Tell us a little bit about your travel goal prior to booking.

The space
The location of Tuindorp Oostzaan in Amsterdam North, 20 minute from the city centre, reachable by a lovely free ferry ride and even closer to the beautiful countryside, together with the ambiance in and around our house, make this spot quite unique. (Please note last ferry to NDSM goed around midnight, after that you take another ferry +bike or uber) Here you get to unwind and relax after a busy day exploring the city buzz or nearby countryside. This will be y
neighborhood_overview:
Our neighbourhood (and especially our sunny street) have an exceptional village feel to them. This village connects the city centre to the North and adds to the typical North-Holland ambiance with nearby canals and the historical NDSM warf within walking distance. There you will also find the IJ Hallen, Europe's largest flee market. Nature reserves Twiske and Ilperveld, as well as Waterland and world-famous Zaanse Schans, are just around the corner. On the other hand, you can reach the center of Amsterdam in under 20 minutes, either by bus or on your rental bicycle (riding the free ferry over the IJ just adds to the joy of living in North and we highly recommend this so that you will experience life as a true local! )

From the Central Station, you take the free ferry to NDSM. . If you have a bicycle, you follow the signs to Twiske. From Central Station you can also take bus 35 to Molenwijk. If you are travelling by car, you take exit S118 towards Tuindorp Oostzaan. Another
host_about: I am a Yoga teacher, Nature Coach and writer from Amsterdam. I love the outdoors, cooking organic meals, animals, travel and cozy places. In the city I like to explore coziness, art, music and people. I balance this with hiking preferably along the seaside or woods. My partner's name is Chun. He is a Math teacher.  We live together in a lovely house in Amsterdam which we also host on Airbnb when we are travelling together. We are a calm and neat couple and respect any place we stay as though it was our own!

name: Bright and Chic Apartment with Cozy Balcony
description:
Welcome to Amsterdam! I’d like to invite you to my cozy apartment in Amsterdam West - De Baarsjes. Just a few minutes away from the flat you can find popular cafes and restaurants and a bustling nightlife with Amsterdam’s historical city center only 15 minutes away. If you’d like to balance your trip with some relaxing time at home, the apartment is well equipped with a modern kitchen, bathroom and a cozy balcony. The latter is a great spot for relaxation from the busy city that awaits outside!

The space
This typical Amsterdam-style apartment is 50m2, located on the 1st floor and consist of three bright rooms, a fully equipped kitchen and a modern bathroom.

The small but cozy bedroom contains a queen size bed (160x200) and a sideboard for you to unpack your bag and store the essentials brought from home.

Next to the bedroom you’ll find the sparsely but beautifully decorated dining and living rooms which in turn is connected to the balcony.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located in the lovely neighbourhood called De Baarsjes, Amsterdam West, and is well connected to Amsterdam city center through tram 13 and 19. The street itself is 100% residential and is almost always quiet in the evening. However, all the conveniences of the city life can be found in the end of the street on both sides (3-5 min walk), that is:

Groceries & ATM (Albert Heijn)
Gym (Gym West)
Public Transport: Tram 19 & 13
Bike Rental
Bakery, Cafés & Restaurants
host_about:
My name is Emil Karlsson, a Swedish expat in the Netherlands, celebrating my 5th year as a citizen of Amsterdam.

When I'm not traveling for work, or leisure, I spend my time this beautiful city that's got so much to offer. Not only history wise (one interest of mine) but also more contemporary cultural activities like art and music.

As I travel often myself, I know how important the accommodation is for the overall travel experience. No matter if you meet me as a guest at your house, or a host at my own, I am always doing my best to meet my one high expectations.

By staying in my home I hope to provide a more unique Amsterdam experience, the same way I have experience so many cities myself.

You are very welcome to contact me for inquiries about me and my apartment and I hope to see you soon in Amsterdam (or elsewhere?)!

Would not recommend the advertise for people above the 50 years old.

name: Private Houseboat~City Center
description:
Our beautiful ship is one of the rare ships who has a quay and is located in the centre of Amsterdam. It's like a oasis in the city: it's quiet, almost no traffic, but 150 meters further and you are in the centre of the jordaan. Haarlemmerstraat, which was called 'best shopping street of Holland', is at 150 meters.

Also nice to know: It's possible to jump from the ship and swim...

All in all the perfect Amsterdam experience!

The space
Central Station is within walking distance.
Our ship is docked in the oldest part of Amsterdam: Prinseneiland / Jordaan.
We have a quay, next to the ship, where you can relax in the sun, till late in the evening. We also have a fire pit at the quay, so you can extend those lovely nights....

We have a big kitchen, with dishwasher, microwave, freezer, etc.
The living room is big as well, we have a television, wifi, WII and a fire place.

In the front of the ship is one (large)
neighborhood_overview:
We think the best thing about our ship is the fact that it's in the center of Amsterdam, but not on the busy canals. So you won't be bothered by people on little or big boats that will float by. The ship is situated in the oldest part of Amsterdam, with the old canalhouses where Amsterdam is famous for. If you walk underneath the railway track, you're immediately in the busy streets of Amsterdam: the Jordaan.
A big supermarket is at 200 feet distance and all sorts of nice shops in the Haarlemmerstraat (best shopping street of Holland 2012).
We have a bicycle which you can use, so you can see all of Amsterdam.
host_about:
We are a family of three, living on our ship in Amsterdam. If you have any special requests for your stay or need information on places to go, eat, drink, please do not hesitate to drop us a line. We will try to answer you as best as we can to make your stay as pleasant and comfortable as possible.

Our ship was build in 1899 and originally used for transportation. Many years ago it was transformed into a beautiful houseboat and now located in the centre of Amsterdam. The Haarlemmerstraat, which was called the best shopping street in The Netherlands in 2012, is 300 meters away. Central Station is within walking distance.
Our ship is docked in the oldest part of Amsterdam: Prinseneiland / Jordaan. 
We have a quay, next to the ship, where you can relax in the sun, till late in the evening. We also have a fire pit at the quay, so you can extend those lovely nights....

We have a big kitchen, with dishwasher, microwave, freezer, etc.
The livingroom is big as well, we have a television, wifi, WII and a wood stove.
In the front of the ship is one (large) bedroom with a bed for two persons and in the back of the ship is also a bed for two persons, a little bit bigger than the other bed.
We have a bathroom with a bathtub and shower.
Washing machine is also available on the ship.
We have two cats. They are both lovely and will stay on the ship.

We have a natural fence of plants around the water, so it is quite safe for little kids. But we also have life vests for the little ones, which is advised.

The ship is docked and not able to sail anymore, so you don't have to be afraid of waking up in the middle of the canal ;)

All in all a great opportunity to experience the Dutch live on a houseboat!

neighborhood_overview:
The Pijp is located directly south of Amsterdam's city centre and it is part of the borough 'Amsterdam-Zuid'. Most street names in the Pijp are named after famous Dutch painters.
The most famous and busiest street market of the Netherlands, the Albert Cuyp Market, is in the Pijp. It is open six days per week and attracts a lot of tourists. The former Heineken brewery is also a popular tourist attraction. Next to the former Heineken brewery is the Marie Heinekenplein, which has a lot of bars and cafes, as well as the near Gerard Douplein.
It used to be Piet Mondriaan's neighborhood back in the day. And many call it the Quartier Latin of Amsterdam for its great vibe and livelyhood.

neighborhood_overview: Traditionally a blue collar neighbourhood just a stone's throw away from the heart of town, 'De Baarsjes', is what one calls 'on the rise'. All around us we see new initiatives popping up; from intimate coffee bars and restaurants, to cool boutiques with local designers. Please ask the staff for inside info on where to go!
host_about:
Hotel Not Hotel is a place in Amsterdam where a room isn’t just a room, but a work of art with its own creator, story, and identity. Most of them designed and specially made by Collaboration-O, a group of young designers that originated from the Eindhoven Design Academy, and one by Arno Coenen and his partner IRIS.

When you wake up, you step into an art-filled, exhibition-like space instead of an anonymous lobby or hallway. The entire hotel is one big living room, with cosy seating areas between the cottages. Combined with our luxury beds and other facilities, Hotel Not Hotel offers an unrivalled experience. 
Besides all this, we feel that the value of a city lies in experiencing its local day-to-day life. As we are closely connected to Amsterdam and its numerous creative entrepreneurs, we know where to send you for a night on the town, a hidden culinary gem, or an upcoming artist’s exhibition. 

The bar connected to Hotel Not Hotel is called Kevin Bacon. Just like the actor, the bar has zero pretention, it always delivers, and it makes sure everybody has a good time.

Kevin Bacon is not your typical hotel bar. It’s where locals get their morning coffee or a quick breakfast. It’s where friends meet for a cocktail or a beer before diving into the nightlife, and where hotel guests let their hair down after a long day in the city.

When the weather is good, the ‘Whitey the White’ terrace is sunny like a perfectly fried egg. The staff’s friendly attitude shines all year round.

name: Private Studio on Spectacular Houseboat
description:
We were able to build our dream. A unique, modern and comfortable houseboat of 35 x 6 meters. We designed an independent private studio in the bow of the boat that can be your's for a few days. So you can share our experience of living the good life on the water. My husband Michael and I live on the other side of the boat.

The space
The nautical boutique style studio is situated in the bow of houseboat "Tasmania". You get your own private space with a private entrance and en-suite bathroom with great shower and toilet. It has underfloor heating and is cosy and warm in the wintertime.

From the bed, you can look at the stars or the full moon. On the private deck you can enjoy a glass of wine and watch the sunset and the beautiful row of old seventeenth century warehouses.
The Tasmania lies at the edge of the city centre in the old woodharbor, a secret hideaway just around the corner of the bustling city centre. Quiet and beautiful, it is situated i
neighborhood_overview: We live in a sheltered harbour just minutes away from the city centre. In the summer we see the sun rise on the port side and the sun set on the starboard side. You can enjoy the sun here alle day. We swim here all summer long and paddle our kayaks. There is also a lot of paddle boarding going on (we don't own one) and lot's of mall boats passing by. There are 2 electrical boat rentals very nearby.
host_about:
Many guests have asked: "What was this boat before you reconverted it?" The answer is simple: it didn't exist. It was custom build. In October 2011 the "Tasmania" arrived in Amsterdam. Our dream came true and we would love to share that dream with you. 

We are hard working film and television professionals. Before building this boat we used to travel a lot. Now every day feels like a holiday. When we are at home we'll be happy to welcome you and tell you everything you want to know about Amsterdam and the boat. But most of the time we're out working. It will make your stay more private. We hope the studio apartment appeals to people who like to travel independent, just like us.

Favorite travel destination: Namibia
Favorite movies: De Rouille et d'Os, Heat, Das Weisse Band and many more.
Favorite Filmfestival: International Documentary Festival Amsterdam (IDFA)
Favorite Music Festivals: Amsterdam Dance Event, North Sea Jazz Festival
Favorite books: Story of a Life by Paustovsky, Innumeracy by Paulos
Favorite food: Mediterranean
Favorite drink: wine, wine, wine. Soon finishing studies at the Wineacademy

name: Amsterdam Farm Lodge: cosy holiday home
description:
Enjoy a very special green setting on the edges of Amsterdam. A sustainable place to stay, to play and to relax. Not too far from the city, yet tranquille and lots off space.

If you come for a drugs vacation, please find another place to stay. This place is not suited for that, we don't allow the use of marihuana at our premesis.

Please read our COVID-19 measures in the description underneath.

The space
Spacious first floor apartment especially suited for families, in a child friendly environment. The 'Amsterdam Farm Lodge' is located on the terrain of the urban farming project 'NoordOogst', a very special place on the edge of Amsterdam, just a few steps away from the hustling and bustling NDSM wharf. But also a lot to see and do on site. Sustainability is important to us, therefore we made use of recycled materials to decorate the place.

The apartment has 3 bedrooms, a living, a dining room, toilet, bathroom and kitchen. Do not e
neighborhood_overview:
We are on the site of an awesome urban farming project, you'll find fields with crops, pigs, chickens, a restaurant, a veggie take-away, kids daycare, natural play ground, woodworking, natural playground, a beekeeper, a wine yard and a brewery. And plenty of space to play.

The hustling and bustling NDSM wharf with is only 15 minutes away by bike, from here the ferry to Central Station departs. Ten minutes biking to the other side you can find nature area 'het Twiske' where you can swim, bike and hike. Only 10 minutes by foot you can discover the hidden nature area of 'Noorder IJplas'. The Zaanse Schans, IJselmeer, beach and 'bollenstreek' are easy to reach.
host_about: We are a couple from Amsterdam and we love to travel. A few years ago we've hosted a wintersport chalet in Austria. We liked it so much that we wanted to open our own B&B. What started out with the idea of a small cabin in the backyard, became much bigger when we got the opportunity of opening the Amsterdam Farm Lodge at the urban farming project of NoordOogst. The Amsterdam Farm Lodge is a project for 10 years and it consists of 7 holiday apartments. Let the adventure begin....

name: Studio Boom Amsterdam
description:
Modern studio apartment, that can accommodate two guests, located in Nieuwmarkt area, in the centre of Amsterdam.

The space
This studio is exceptionally bright and exceptionally spacious with large windows, high ceilings and wooden floors providing a classical feel, while the contemporary furnishings bring the space into the modern era. The living space features a sofa, armchair, coffee table, dining table with seating for four and a flat screen television. The four metre high windows in the living room provide an amazing view of the canal and the Nieuwmarkt. The kitchenette is equipped with a microwave, fridge, a toaster and a coffee machine. The romantic mezzanine(4.6 feet high) is where you will find the sleeping quarters, complete with two single beds that can easily be joined together, and a view over the rest of the apartment. The bathroom is contemporary and comes with a shower, washbasin and toilet. Located in the Nieuwmarkt area, this apartment is ideal
neighborhood_overview: This apartment is located in Nieuwmarkt in the centre of Old Amsterdam. Nieuwmarkt square is filled with shops, cafes, bars and the popular market. It is home to De Waag, an old weight house that used to form part of the city walls constructed in 1481. During the 16th century boats would stop here, unload their goods, weigh them and pay the required taxes. Today the building houses a restaurant and is a great place to stop for a drink on a warm afternoon. The centre of Amsterdam, Dam Square, can be reached on foot and is home to the stunning Royal Palace, Madame Tussauds, the New Church and De Bijenkorf department store. For art lovers Rembrandt House is just a short distance from the apartment and it is here he lived and worked for many years. Many of the major attractions are within walking distance of the apartment, while the Metro and trams provide public transport options allowing you to get to any part of the city with ease.

description:
Chique and luxurious ground floor appartment with two bedrooms, huge living room gourmet kitchen, bathroom and small garden. Quiet location nearby the river 'Amstel', within walking distance from great city trips and bars/restaurants, close to public transportation. The perfect appartment for a couple with children! Our appartment provides sleeping space for five adults, or for instance three adults and two children, due to flexible sleeping options. We'd love to hear from you!

The space
This ground floor appartment, built in 1932, was a tobacco store in the earlier days. The house therefore is still very spacious and light; with huge windows and high ceilings (3.20 meters). The house was newly renovated in June 2015 with a brandnew gourmet kitchen, bathroom, toilet and wooden(oak) floor.

It now offers you all the luxury you would want for your getaway while you can still enjoy the authentic Amsterdam feeling.

The 112m2 house offers you a
neighborhood_overview:
The impressive river 'de Amstel' is just at the end of the street. A gorgeous stroll alongside the river towards the trending and energetic area 'De Pijp' or the city centre shows you Amsterdam at her best!

Many restaurants and bars are within walking distance from the house. We will tell you which ones to visit to experience the real Dutch experience, and not the touristy one! :-) If you want to, we can help you with your reservations. Both higher end restaurants as informal places to eat are just around the corner.

A ten minute walk towards a big supermarket with anything you need: Albert Heijn.

The neighborhood is quiet. Sometimes on Friday and Saturday nights you will hear some noice of people walking towards the train station around 11pm/midnight. But it has never really bothered us.
host_about:
Hi fellow traveler! 

We are Bas and Mirte, around 35 yrs old and we live in Amsterdam with our two little kids ages 2 and 4.
Our motto for life is work hard, play hard: Mirte is a marketing manager in FMCG and Bas is owner of a paragliding school. Enough about work; we both love to travel, far away or closeby. Bas loves paragliding and visits the beach and dunes at least once a week to fly; even more he loves paragliding in the Alps, so if he's not enjoying Amsterdam; chances are you'll find him in Austria or Italy. I myself love cooking, running (great combination ;-)), shopping and reading. And I hate how boring my life looks compared to Bas' ;-). 
Oh and we do have other things in common, we both love watching movies and series! 

We bought our house in March '15. With an extensive renovation (in both time and euro's) we turned it into our perfect little Amsterdam-palace  and we treat it with care. We will take good care of your house, and expect you to do the same with ours.

neighborhood_overview:
Watergraafsmeer is a neat, popular, very child friendly (the place to live in Amsterdam if you have kids) neighborhood. Your kids will have a great time here because there's a small playground facing the house and a very big, famous playground "Mariotteplein" at 250 m. Enjoy a family dinner in the child friendly restaurant "Ginger & Ale" just 200 meters from our home. For breakfast, lunch or a coffee go to lunchroom/asian deli "lastig". It has a playroom for the kids so you can have some peace and quiet ;-)
Artis, the famous zoo is very close too. Our area features mainly 1920's and 1930's construction and is very green. Beautiful parcs "Frankendael": 400 m. and "Oosterpark" 1400 m. Both great for walks or barbecues/picknicks.

If you want to go to the city center you just walk to the end of our street and hop on tram line 19 which will take you there in about 15 minutes.

There are many nice shops and a big supermarket closeby.

neighborhood_overview: Traditionally a blue collar neighbourhood just a stone's throw away from the heart of town, 'De Baarsjes', is what one calls 'on the rise'. All around us we see new initiatives popping up; from intimate coffee bars and restaurants, to cool boutiques with local designers. Please ask the staff for inside info on where to go!
host_about:
Hotel Not Hotel is a place in Amsterdam where a room isn’t just a room, but a work of art with its own creator, story, and identity. Most of them designed and specially made by Collaboration-O, a group of young designers that originated from the Eindhoven Design Academy, and one by Arno Coenen and his partner IRIS.

When you wake up, you step into an art-filled, exhibition-like space instead of an anonymous lobby or hallway. The entire hotel is one big living room, with cosy seating areas between the cottages. Combined with our luxury beds and other facilities, Hotel Not Hotel offers an unrivalled experience. 
Besides all this, we feel that the value of a city lies in experiencing its local day-to-day life. As we are closely connected to Amsterdam and its numerous creative entrepreneurs, we know where to send you for a night on the town, a hidden culinary gem, or an upcoming artist’s exhibition. 

The bar connected to Hotel Not Hotel is called Kevin Bacon. Just like the actor, the bar has zero pretention, it always delivers, and it makes sure everybody has a good time.

Kevin Bacon is not your typical hotel bar. It’s where locals get their morning coffee or a quick breakfast. It’s where friends meet for a cocktail or a beer before diving into the nightlife, and where hotel guests let their hair down after a long day in the city.

When the weather is good, the ‘Whitey the White’ terrace is sunny like a perfectly fried egg. The staff’s friendly attitude shines all year round.

name: SWEETS hotel Meeuwenpleinbrug
description:
A 1960s bridge house perched between a neighbourhood park and a bustling intersection in Amsterdam North; a perfect overnight stop for cyclists on the LF7 cycle route. Explore the hottest spots in the city with the new North-South metro line; station 'Noorderpark' is right across the street! (2 minutes to Amsterdam Central Station) Or discover trendy Amsterdam North with the Eye Film Museum, A'DAM Lookout and De Ceuvel. In summer, the neighbouring Noorderpark is a popular leafy oasis for locals.

The space
From 1969 to 2017, bridge house Meeuwenpleinbrug accommodated the city’s bridge keepers, who opened and closed the bridge for passing waterway traffic. In 2017, when the local government centralized bridge control, the bridge house started a new chapter as one of the 28 suites of SWEETS hotel. As with every SWEET, Meeuwenpleinbrug's interior is inspired by its architectural history.

Architect 1969: Dirk Sterenberg
Architect 2017: Space&Matter
neighborhood_overview: Meeuwenpleinbrug is located in Amsterdam North - a neighbourhood that has become increasingly popular over the past few years. With free ferries crossing the river IJ and the new North-South metro line up and running, it is faster and easier than ever to get to Amsterdam centre. But why would you, if there's so much to do and see in Meeuwenpleinbrug's vicinity? The relaxing Noorderpark is right next to your bridge, and eco-hub and restaurant De Ceuvel – one of Amsterdam's most innovative projects – is just around the corner. Check out our city guide for more recommendations!
host_about:
SWEETS hotel is a one-of-a-kind hotel located across Amsterdam in 28 different bridge houses. Each bridge house has been transformed into an independent hotel suite that accommodates a maximum of two guests.

For centuries, Amsterdam’s bridge houses accommodated the city’s many bridge keepers who were responsible for opening the impressive structures for passing water traffic. With building dates between 1673 and 2009, the bridge houses carry an extensive history. Visiting them in chronological order is like a journey through time: their various architectural styles reveal how the city developed and grew, when new quarters were built and even how people thought about city development at that time.

With the hotel room interiors, SWEETS hotel offers guests a unique and comfortable living space, while keeping the history of every bridge house in mind. All bridge houses are different, and so are the interiors. Every SWEET accommodates up to two adults and contains a kingsize double bed, a bathroom and coffee and tea facilities.

SWEETS hotel, first initiated in 2012 as an urban space project, is 8 years in the making. Over half of the 28 bridge houses are currently available for reservations, with more coming soon.

SWEETS hotel is an initiative and co-creation of the architecture office Space&Matter (known for De Ceuvel, an ecological hub), project development partner Grayfield and Suzanne Oxenaar and Otto Nan of Seven New Things, founders of Lloyd Hotel & Cultural Embassy (the world’s first 1- to 5-star hotel) and Hotel The Exchange.
