The quaint and quirky streets that straddle Amsterdam’s grandest canals form the city’s most photogenic micro-neighbourhood. Known to locals as De Negen Straatjes or ‘The Nine Streets’, this special neighbourhood is full to bursting with vintage and designer shopping, speciality stores and cosy cafés. In the Stary night room you have an amazing street view. Because of the big windows a lot of light is allowed to enter the room and give you a great chance to see the typical Amsterdam homes.
host_about:
Whether you are visiting Amsterdam for the first time or you have visited it before, you will always
find something new in this city full of history. Let us introduce you to this magnificent place in
another way!

We are Maria and Aurora. We met years ago in this same amazing and fabulous city, a city where
dreams come true. Here's something about us too:
I am Maria and I am an aspiring illustrator and I am also a mother. I have a Master Degree in plastic arts , fine arts and art history. After spending time abroad, I decided to stay and live in Holland. Apart from my love for art, I have always dreamed of having a small hotel where I can meet interesting people. What could be better than to be in such a fabulous and artistic city as Amsterdam! I have been away from this wonderful city and country for a short time. But it didn't take long before I came back to Amsterdam to rediscover it. Anyone who has been to Amsterdam one time, always comes back!

I am Aurora and I am a fashion branding manager and PR expert. Fashion is my passion. I have more than 15 years experience in the fashion retail industry and B2B events. I have developed several PR activities for fashion showrooms, international designers, brands, individual press shows and shows for fashion platforms. In addition to my professional love for fashion, I, as a mother, love home comfort and want to pass this love on to you and make you feel at home.

neighborhood_overview:
The neigbourhood was planned by the famous dutch town planner Van Eesteren. He made the Garden City. As a result the neighbourhood is very green and quiet. Even little children can play outdoors. There is a playground in front of the house.

There is a good sense of community and it's a very safe area. You will enjoy a good nights' rest in our house as there won't be any city noises to keep you from sleeping. And during the day you will be able to reach the center very quick and easy. Shops and restaurants are at walking distance.

There are good facilities for sports (olympic swimming pool, lake, quiet roads ideal for running and biking). Though we live close to the centre of Amsterdam, the countryside with its typical polders (grasslands) is next door. The beach is at 25 km.

1930s terraced estate between two large parks, just off the main road down to the port. Close to the buzz of the centre of town but amazingly quiet.

Two large parks 5 minutes walk away, a shopping centre and various supermarkets within 15 minutes walking distance.
host_about:
I'm English but Amsterdam has been my home since 2013.  Before that I lived in Palma de Mallorca, Spain.  

I bought my house here in Amsterdam Noord in October 2017, since when I've done a lot of renovation/redecoration and have enjoyed hosting guests from all over the world for since 2018.  I've used Airbnb on my own travels over the year and love the flexibility and opportunity to meet new people.  

Amsterdam is a truly great city: full of interesting corners, well-organised, diverse, cutting-edge and free-thinking.  Noord is the best area of town, down-to-earth, uncrowded and green but with swift access to the city centre.

host_about: Generator Amsterdam is located in the up-and-coming eastern side of the city, overlooking Oosterpark. This former zoological university building can accommodate 564 guests in 168 twin and quadruple rooms, with en-suite bathrooms and incredible views of the surrounding area. There is also one luxury apartment for six people, with views of the park and a self-catered kitchen. It has flexible and spacious social areas, filled with creative design touches like glass-fronted elevators, a light and airy café and an outdoor terrace. We’ve turned the former lecture hall into an impressive chill-out lounge and bar, while the old library is now a relaxation and private events room. The basement and café are now dining destinations and the original boiler room has become a secret late night bar.

neighborhood_overview:
In de buurt zijn op loopafstand verschillende supermarkten (Deen, Lidl en AH), restaurantjes, apotheek, winkelcentrum. Groter winkelcentrum Buikslotermeerplein is 10 minuten met de auto. Het NDSM-terrein, met vele festiviteiten en restaurantjes is 10 minuten fietsen, het EYE-filmmuseum 15 minuten. Noord kent vele leuke restaurants aan het IJ. Op woensdag is het markt in de van der Pekstraat.
Het centrum is op de fiets via de pont (NDSM of Buiksloterweg)over het IJ heel goed te bereiken. Heerlijk voor vertier en daarna lekker de rust weer in. De pont vaart de hele nacht door. Er zijn meerdere goede (nacht)busverbindingen met het centrum en de rest van de omgeving. Het is prachtig fietsen in de landelijke omgeving. Recreatiegebied het Twiske ligt om de hoek. Sloepen te huur in Oostzaan en Amsterdam.
Met de auto zijn de Zaanse Schans, Monickendam, Volendam ed snel bereikbaar.

THE WESTERPARK AREA
The area has a varied mix of independent shops, old-school street markets, shiny new restaurants, traditional brown cafés and young expat and Amsterdammer families.

THE WESTERPARK (a 5 minute walk)
The modern and exciting, 14-hectare city park that surrounds the Westergasfabriek buildings is not only a perfect place to relax in natural surroundings, but also a venue for digital art and culture.

THE JORDAAN (a 10 minute walk)
The Jordaan is nothing but highlights. Maze-like streets offer hidden courtyards, cafes (both traditional and trendy), art galleries and pleasantly nosy neighbors. One also has access to some of the more scenic outdoor markets in the country. In particular, Noordermarkt has a flea market on Monday mornings and an organic farmers' market on Saturdays.

neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located really close to the Jordaan Area. The Jordaan district is the city center of Amsterdam, known by its beautiful houses, nice restaurants and shops. The canals of Amsterdam are located here as well.

In the Jordaan, there are several markets you can visit. Every Monday, there is a flea market at the Noordermarkt. It is the perfect spot to buy Dutch plates, pots and linen. They are also selling clothes and accessories. For a foodmarket, you can go to the Lindenmarkt at the Lindengracht on Saturdays, to the Westerstraat market on Mondays or to the Biological foodmarket at the Noordermarkt on Saturdays.

The Westertoren is one of the landmarks of the Jordaan. It's really worth to visit and climb! Also close by: Anne Frank Huis, Dam, Royal Palace.

Nice to know: each of the streets is named after a flower.

This part of Amsterdam has buildings like the Royal Concertgebouw, the Rijksmuseum, the Van Gogh museum and the Stedelijk Museum, all situated around the Museumplein. The city’s ‘green lung’ of Vondelpark remains Amsterdam’s most densely populated place-to-be whenever the sun shines. name: SWEETS hotel Van Hallbrug
description:
Tiny and typical 1930s bridge house with lots of daylight and an amazing view. Situated in the quiet ‘Staatslieden’ neighbourhood, yet right next to the Jordaan area and close to Amsterdam Centre (15 min) and Westerpark (10 min). The surrounding neighbourhood offers an endless number of shopping, dining and sightseeing options that are worth a visit. Heads up tiny house lovers: this is SWEETS hotel’s tiniest bridge house (only 10,5 m2) with the tiniest bathroom. For curious travellers!

The space
From 1932 to 2017, bridge house ‘Van Hallbrug’ accommodated the city’s many bridge keepers. In 2017, the bridge house started a new chapter as one of SWEETS hotel's 28 hotel rooms. As with every SWEET, Van Hallbrug’s interior is inspired by its architectural history.

Architect 1932: Pieter Lodewijk Kramer
Architect 2017: Space&Matter
Architectural Style: Amsterdam School
Waterway: Kostverlorenvaart
Bridge Type: Bascule bridge

The
neighborhood_overview: The surrounding neighbourhood of bridge house Van Hallbrug offers an endless number of shopping, dining and sightseeing options that are worth a visit – all within walking or cycling distance. Just cross the bridge and you’ll find a small square with great places to get your morning coffee (Back to Black) or a delicious vegetarian meal (Vleesch noch Visch). Westerpark, the park where locals go for a festival or picnic, is at a 10-minute walk from the bridge house. Check out our self-composed Neighbourhood Guide on the tablet in the room for more recommendations!
host_about:
SWEETS hotel is a one-of-a-kind hotel located across Amsterdam in 28 different bridge houses. Each bridge house has been transformed into an independent hotel suite that accommodates a maximum of two guests.

For centuries, Amsterdam’s bridge houses accommodated the city’s many bridge keepers who were responsible for opening the impressive structures for passing water traffic. With building dates between 1673 and 2009, the bridge houses carry an extensive history. Visiting them in chronological order is like a journey through time: their various architectural styles reveal how the city developed and grew, when new quarters were built and even how people thought about city development at that time.

With the hotel room interiors, SWEETS hotel offers guests a unique and comfortable living space, while keeping the history of every bridge house in mind. All bridge houses are different, and so are the interiors. Every SWEET accommodates up to two adults and contains a kingsize double bed, a bathroom and coffee and tea facilities.

SWEETS hotel, first initiated in 2012 as an urban space project, is 8 years in the making. Over half of the 28 bridge houses are currently available for reservations, with more coming soon.

SWEETS hotel is an initiative and co-creation of the architecture office Space&Matter (known for De Ceuvel, an ecological hub), project development partner Grayfield and Suzanne Oxenaar and Otto Nan of Seven New Things, founders of Lloyd Hotel & Cultural Embassy (the world’s first 1- to 5-star hotel) and Hotel The Exchange.

description:
A spacious, comfortable, beautifully designed private apartment with garden access in Amsterdam. Sleeps 2-4. Situated near the centre of Amsterdam in a quiet friendly neighbourhood with a good selection of restaurants and shops and parks.

The space
A spacious, comfortable, beautifully designed private apartment with garden access in Amsterdam.
The bedroom has a double bed 160/200cm (or two separate beds 80x200cm) and in the sitting room is a very comfortable couch which can be turned into a bed of 160/200cm. neighborhood_overview:
Amsterdam's District of Oost ('east') encompasses the areas of Plantage, Oosterparkbuurt, Indische buurt, Dapperbuurt and Amstel. Oost is strikingly green and spacious, yet it also has plenty of sights and opportunities for shopping, eating and drinking on offer.

For busy Amsterdam nightlife you can easily take the tram into the city centre but for a good meal and a pleasant evening out there is a great selection in our neighborhood which is home to some of the city's most highly-regarded restaurants: De Kas (who grow food in their own greenhouses), Merkelbach (slowfood in a park) and Riva (with beautiful views over the Amstel River).
In addition there are also a lot of smaller less expensive restaurants just around the corner.
host_about:

neighborhood_overview:
Our house is situated in a street that gives access to the Vondelpark, which is a treat in itself. This also opens up the possibility to walk to the museum district (The Modern Art Museum, Van Gogh Museum and the National Museum), a 15-minutes' walk from our house. Leidseplein, with its bars, cinemas and theatres is also a 15-minutes' walk from our house, although if it is pubs you are after, you may just as well grab a beer at Draft and Craft around the corner.
Our street gives access to the renowned and stately Vondelpark where you can have a drink and a chat either at the "Blauwe Theehuis" (Blue Tea House), the "Groot Melkhuis" (The Milkhouse) or the "Vondeltuin". Apart from that, you could also have a picnic at the park or just chill out. At the corner Overtoom - Kattenlaantje you could rent inline skates to make your way through the park in a sporty manner.

description:
Actually, I wanted to spend even more on each room, the furniture, the decoration and the many details... my husband and I just didn't seem to be on the same page. But I love my little hideaway in the middle of Amsterdam. Our neighbours in this place full of history are all native ones. Lawyers, midwives, judges, journalists and creative people live here close together - right in the city centre and yet away from the noise and bustle of the unbelievably many tourists.

The space
I want to give you a sense of "home" in these rooms. Modern, high-quality furnishings, designer pieces and especially many small details selected with love. Whenever I have found great pieces at a flea market again, I hope that you as guests will enjoy them.

In addition to the large terrace for all guests on the second floor, there is also the communal kitchen on the ground floor right at the entrance (then you do not have to carry the groceries far!) There is a record player -
neighborhood_overview:
Living by the canal - that is a dream for many. In the past, however, this was considered frowned upon and not classical enough. Therefore the canal was filled up around 16th century. A beautiful park in the middle of the city was created - and still is today. Large trees that provide shade in summer and absorb the sounds of the city.
I love the Cafe Slijterij Oosterling (50m from us). Open since 1877, this is probably one of the most authentic places in Amsterdam. Time seems to stand still here. If you are hungry, you can get delicious sandwiches, burgers, salads or freshly caught fish in the Brasserie Nel (400m). If you prefer self-catering and our shared kitchen, the supermarket is only 70m away.

description:
Welcome to our lovely home! You've come to the right place to experience Amsterdam as it is - a stylish family home in a lovely neighboorhood in Amsterdam City Center.

The space
We offer a child friendly home (120ft²) that easily accomodates 3 adults and 3 children, or a maximum of 4 adults.

Our house is on the ground floor so easy accessible. The entire appartment is quite large and consists of two floors. Please note we have steep stairs, as most Amsterdam houses. You will have the whole home to yourself.

On the ground floor is a toilet, large living room with a fireplace and open kitchen with a large family table with place for six adults. One children chair available.

THE NEIGHBORHOOD:

We are in the city centre in a quiet neighbourhood (Helmersbuurt). The neighbourhood is very popular and known for its nice bars, restaurants and plenty of facilities for families with children. Recently new (coffee) bars have been opened around the corner and across the street is one of the best bakeries in Amsterdam; 't Vlaams Broodhuys.

We are in walking distance from the Vondelpark (famous its quiet places, great terraces and free concerts) with and many other attractions such as the museum square, Leidse Square, Jordaan, the famous 'negen straatjes' and pop venue Paradiso. The high class PC Hooftstraat shopping street is also in walking distance.

Paid parking space is widely available in our street. There are several supermarkets (discount, organic and 'normal') in our area, all within a three minutes walk. You can take a 10 min bike ride (or just one of the trams close to our home) to the Albert Cuip Market or the Dam Square and
host_about:
I am a mom of three and a web designer. We love living in the city in our  spacious and cosy home in the middle of the city. I can't live without my family, friends, music, my IPhone and my home town Amsterdam. 

My style of travelling is 'live like the locals do' - try to get off the beaten track by just walking around town or asking advice to local people in a bar or grocery store. I love to make myself at home and offer the possibilities for other people to do the same when they visit me. Oh, and I am crazy about lighthouses...

neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood is very peaceful, safe and family-friendly. It has a bit of a village vibe inside a bigger city. The direct neighborhood is considered upscale, with lots of families with children living in the area.

There is a playground directly around the corner, with a picnic area and the possibility to swim in the dock during summer.

There is also a traditional Dutch snackbar (Febo), and a bike rental (Halfords) just around the corner and an outisde neighborhood (farmers') market every Wednesday, Friday and Saturday, called 'Pekmarkt'.

The market, and closest supermarket, grocery shops and stores are located at Mosveld, a 10-15 minute walk or a 3-4 minute bike ride.
The opening hours from the supermarket (Albert Heijn) are 7-22 and 8-22 during the weekend, also on Sunday!

It is very easy to get to the house from the Central Station.

Once you cross the IJ canal, it is 10-15 minute walk or 4 minute bike ride to the loca
host_about:
Hi! We are Eva & Kobe.  

You’re more than welcome to stay at one of the fabulous apartments and homes we manage while the home owners are on holiday. 

We like to think we offer the best of both worlds: you can enjoy a one-of-a-kind vacation experience in a unique property, without compromising on service and convenience.

We strive to offer you a pleasant and memorable stay in our home town: Amsterdam. We love to share the hidden gems with you, and we can provide you with all the information you need to get the most out of your stay. 

As we were awarded the 'superhost' status on airbnb, we can assure you that we will do our outmost to make your stay truly amazing. Please feel free to have a look at our 800+ reviews!

Our core values are similar to the ones on which airbnb is founded, hospitality & live like a local is what's is all about. We are flexible, always available and will welcome you in person, show you around and answer all of your questions.  Exceptions with us offering a self check-in can be made during 2020.

Combined with the fact that our standards of cleanliness are very high, you can certainly expect our properties to be 100% clean. All our high quality bath- and bed linen are professionally cleaned and ironed.  

Please feel free to contact us if you have any questions or special requests. We'll be happy to assist you! We would be delighted to host you during your stay in Amsterdam!

description:

0363 5C38 6771 9863 C043
neighborhood_overview: Welcome to my house boat, located in the rapidly upcoming popular Amsterdam Noord area, just north of central station. A 15 minute walk (or 5 minute bike ride) from the Amsterdam tower, Central Station and the NDSM area. Surrounded by popular gems like "de Ceuvel", restaurant "de klaproos", Cinema "FC Hyena", "Monk"climbing hall, the "Van der Pek" street market, there is a lot of interesting stuff going on in the area. And yet, this floating sustainably built village is an oasis of tranquility in Amsterdam. Developed and built by its inhabitants these 30 houseboats form Europe's most sustainable floating neighborhood are home to 46 families in a tight knit community. Go for a swim outside, take the kayak for a ride, take a stroll in nearby Noorderpark, or take the bike up to the country side not far away.
host_about: I'm a filmmaker from amsterdam. I like arts, restaurants, travelling, concerts. I am also the founding father of this sustainable floating community called ‘Schoonschip’ in Amsterdam.

neighborhood_overview: Traditionally a blue collar neighbourhood just a stone's throw away from the heart of town, 'De Baarsjes', is what one calls 'on the rise'. All around us we see new initiatives popping up; from intimate coffee bars and restaurants, to cool boutiques with local designers. Please ask the staff for inside info on where to go!
host_about:
Hotel Not Hotel is a place in Amsterdam where a room isn’t just a room, but a work of art with its own creator, story, and identity. Most of them designed and specially made by Collaboration-O, a group of young designers that originated from the Eindhoven Design Academy, and one by Arno Coenen and his partner IRIS.

When you wake up, you step into an art-filled, exhibition-like space instead of an anonymous lobby or hallway. The entire hotel is one big living room, with cosy seating areas between the cottages. Combined with our luxury beds and other facilities, Hotel Not Hotel offers an unrivalled experience. 
Besides all this, we feel that the value of a city lies in experiencing its local day-to-day life. As we are closely connected to Amsterdam and its numerous creative entrepreneurs, we know where to send you for a night on the town, a hidden culinary gem, or an upcoming artist’s exhibition. 

The bar connected to Hotel Not Hotel is called Kevin Bacon. Just like the actor, the bar has zero pretention, it always delivers, and it makes sure everybody has a good time.

Kevin Bacon is not your typical hotel bar. It’s where locals get their morning coffee or a quick breakfast. It’s where friends meet for a cocktail or a beer before diving into the nightlife, and where hotel guests let their hair down after a long day in the city.

When the weather is good, the ‘Whitey the White’ terrace is sunny like a perfectly fried egg. The staff’s friendly attitude shines all year round.

neighborhood_overview:
The Groenburgwal is a canal in Amsterdam that connects the Raamgracht with the Amstel. The Groenburgwal is parallel to the Kloveniersburgwal and the Zwanenburgwal, in the shadow of the tower of the Zuiderkerk.

The area between the Kloveniersburgwal and the Zwanenburgwal was until late in the 16th century "the site outside the fortress at the Amstel". In 1593 the area was added to the city.

Cloth weavers worked here. The wool was washed, carded and spun, then cloth was woven from it. After fulling and dyeing the cloth was tensioned on wooden frames to dry and stretch. The names of the nearby Raamgracht, the Raamsloot near Rusland, dug in 1537, and the Verversstraat (1593) recall those activities.

In the early 17th century, the Amstel between Kloveniersburgwal and Groenburgwal and a little later the 's Gravelandse Veer, between Groenburgwal and Blauwbrug, was compressed. Around that time the name Groenburgwal was born; green dyers were specially establish

neighborhood_overview:
This is a charming, relax and quiet neighbourhood with beautiful historic houses. The shopping area Oostpoort is within walking distance and public transport (tram 9) taking you to the heart of Amsterdam is around the corner. There are a number of beautiful parks in this area (Oosterpark and Park Frankendael).

In the surrounding neighbourhood you can find everything that makes your weekend break or longer stay in Amsterdam comfortable and enjoyable. Within walking distance there is a selection of cafe's and delicious take-away. Restaurants range from local to Marroccan, Italian and Surinam kitchen.
There are convenience stores such as Albert Heijn and Vomar (opening hours from 8 am until 10 pm).
Furthermore you will find the new shopping area called Oostpoort, with a lot of shops, restaurants, several bakeries, an eco-food store etc.

name: Avontuur ...a special way to spend the night!
description:
On board of this beautiful old dutch klipper 'Avontuur' you will find a cozy and comfortable place to stay right in the heart of Amsterdam.
The Avontuur (built in 1908) is moored at a quiet spot at the Westerdok.
Only a stone's throw away from the hustle and bustle of the old city center.
The B&B is at the stern of the ship overlooking the Westerdok canal.

The space
The B&B is in the deckhouse, at the stern (rear) part of the ship.
On the sterndeck you have a private and sunny area where you can sit and relax,
and enjoy the view of the Westerdok and the passing little boats.
From the sterndeck you have access to the deckhouse.
The deckhouse is renovated and converted into a romantic and cosy B&B with a double bed (160x200) and a private shower and toilet.
There's a counter with sink and and a fridge, a Nespresso coffeemaker & waterboiler.

*Bedding & towels will be provided
*Free WiFi
*Hairdryer
neighborhood_overview:
The Westerdok is a new, trendy neighbourhood in the heart of Amsterdam, less than a 10 minutes walk from Central Station and 5 minutes walk from the cozy Jordaan area.

The Jordaan area is one of the oldest parts of Amsterdam with many little shops, cafés, restaurants and galeries.

At the Haarlemmerdijk (5 min.) you'll find a.o. a fresh bakery and a supermarket.

On Saturdays a popular organic farmers' market is held at the Noordermarkt (10 min.)

The 9 Streets: nine cozy and pitoresque shopping streets in the middle of the Unesco Heritage canal belt.

The Dam-square, Anne Frank house & the Nine Streets are all at approximately 20 minutes walking distance.

At the Westerpark (15 min.) there's always plenty to do. You'll find cafés, restaurants, clubs, a cinema, and many nice places to hang out.

With the lively old city at only a 5 minutes walk and the peace on board of this beautiful Klipper your stay in Amsterda

Before everybody wanted to live on the canals but since the area has been overtaken by noise and partying people this became the place to live with very good restaurants,  great shops, Concerthall and all the Musea around the corner including the convenient Airport Shuttle bus 397 which takes and brings you direct from the airport, only a few minute walk from my house. 
A lot of my quests take a morning jog in the nearby Vondelpark....
I have lived for twenty years abroad and returned  4years ago.
Before that I have been a stewardess with KLM for fourteen years so I can say receiving people comes natural to me :-) and  it is most important that my quests feel at home.
I hope to welcome you in the near future.....
Regards Roszica

host_about:
Born in Copenhagen, architecture and design are my life. I regularly work with major Nordic design studios and during one of my trips I stopped off in Barcelona: I was captivated by its architecture, culture and Mediterranean colour. Such was the impact the city had on me that I decided to stay and carry on my latest project: Eric Vökel Boutique Apartments. 

Each of the apartments has been personally designed and decorated by me as if they might become my own home.

Welcome home!

Eric, 
Arquitect and designer

name: Cozy sleeping in popular Amsterdam West
description:
My trendy and comfortable apartment on the westside of Amsterdam will give you a perfect stay in a great neighborhood. Within 5 minutes you can have a picknick in the famous Erasmusparc, have a nice drink on a terrace or eat at a cozy restaurant!

The space
This apartment has one bedroom,a bathroom, a huge living room, a kitchen and two balconies and is about 60m2. There is free internet.

The apartment is 3 minutes from the Erasmuspark, nearby the famous West area Baarsjes, Westerpark and cosy Jordaan district. From the apartment to the city centre (Dam-square) it's only ten minutes with the tram or bus. Public transport is on the corner and bike renting is also on the corner.

Around Westerpark you find some interesting shops, restaurant and long canals where is great to visit during the summer and some lovely pubs. The Jordaan is ofcourse the heart of the city and is an attraction you must not miss.

The neighbourhood is called Bos
neighborhood_overview:
This neighborhood is fantastic! The Baarsjes is on the corner with really nice restaurants, shops and cafés. Also the Westerpark and the Erasmuspark is the best in spring and summertime.
If you come i will look up all the nice things to do during the days you will stay in Amsterdam. So you won't miss a thing :-)
host_about:
Hello!

I am Marij de Vries, 39 years young and living in Amsterdam. In 2010 i bought my own appartment in the west of Amsterdam. I work as an Eventmanager at a marketing and salesoffice in Amsterdam. In my sparetime i love doing different kinds of sports, hangout with my friends and playing the guitar. During summer you will find me very often in the parc and festivals.
I also love to travel. I have been to Thailand, Indonesia, Cambodia, Malaysia, Vietnam, China, Panama, Laos, Nepal, India en lot's of places in Europe. 

For you as a guest i don't have to tell you about how great it will be for you to stay in Amsterdam! From my place to the centre of Amsterdam it's 10 minutes with the tram or, if you dare, on the biclycle :-)

name: Cosy & comfortable suite on coaster close 2 centre
description:
Cosy & comfortable houseboat apartment for a couple or 2 friends. Offering private entrance, living room with sofa bed, kitchenette, bathroom and bedroom. The light and very well insulated 35m2 studio is situated in the former sailors cabin of coaster Mado. On top you’ll have your private deck located directly on the local swimming pond with magnificent view over the harbor. Just 1-5 minutes walking to lot’s of bars, restaurants, shopping mall and bus + tramlines direct to historical center.

The space
The bright 3-room 35m2 apartment with high ceilings includes a living room with soda bed, kitchenette, bathroom and bedroom with double bed. The living room offers high speed wi-fi, Chrome cast 42” digital TV and sound system for streaming your Netflix and Spotify, comfortable under flour heating, ventilation and a sofa bed for 2 kids. Kitchen has a micro wave, tea kettle, Nespresso and refrigerator with freezer for preparing light meals (no cooking). The bathroom i
neighborhood_overview: Coaster Mado is moored on KNSM island that is part of the Eastern Docklands in the centre of Amsterdam. Merchants and world travellers used to depart from here to the East Indies, the United States and Surinam. Today KNSM island is known for its modern architecture, interior design shops and waterside cafes. It offers a perfect combination of relaxation, character and the liveliness of the city. We recommend to take your breakfast with commuters in Bakkerswinkel Neeltje, drink a beer with locals in Cafe De Zuid or dine with Dutch celebrities at the Harbour Club.
host_about: It is a pleasure inviting you on our Coaster Mado. Living on a boat gives us a holiday feeling year round, which we would like to share with you. During the day we are busy with work and our kids are at school, but we are happy to answer any question before and during your stay. We all love to go sailing and swimming. Marieke, Sander & kids.

neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is situated in 'Oud-West', a lively area west of the city centre and bordering the famous Jordaan neighbourhood. The area has a lot to offer, regardless what you are looking for, and is a good base to discover the city from.

Some highlights within walking distance include:
- Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh museum, Stedelijk museum and Moco
- Foodhallen; a food market style restaurant area with a cinema next door
- Vondelpark, and a little further away the Westerpark and Rembrandtpark
- Anne Frank House
- Loads of restaurants, bars and coffee places

And as there is no better way to see Amsterdam than from the canals it's worth mentioning there is a boat rental place right in front of the house!

Windows on the first floor are large allowing for light to enter throughout the day and offer a good view of the immediate neighbourhood.

name: Sonder | Park House | King Suite
description:
Museums, shopping, and stroopwafels. Your Amsterdam experience begins at Park House. Walk out the door onto smooth stone steps and venture a block to PC Hooftstraat home to Versace, Gucci, Cartier, and more. Inhale fresh fragrances from ICI PARIS XL on the most luxurious shopping street in the Netherlands. Picturesque brick buildings guide you to the compelling city centre 200 meters away, infused with notable sites and eclectic eateries. Browse the magnificent walls of Rijksmuseum where impressive collections of European art come to life. Return home as melodic music escapes from nearby Vondelpark Openluchttheater and grasps your ears. Conclude your night with a cocktail on the calming garden terrace. Or laze in the à la mode lounge with your favorite book and reminisce on the day’s affairs. Your private room awaits, calling you to a restful sleep. 

The space
Working, relaxing, living. Our spaces have all the other essentials you need for your stay.
neighborhood_overview: Oud-Zuid is the best-kept secret in Amsterdam. And we're giving you the scoop. Bordering the historic center, this trendy neighborhood has the ideal combination of upscale boutiques and memorable museums. Spend your day relaxing in the beautiful greenery of Vondelpark, listening to music spilling from the open-air theater. Or stroll down charming tree-lined streets to admire the stunning 19th-century mansions. Ready for some shopping? Check out P.C. Hooftstraat. Formally named after a Dutch poet and playwright, this luxurious street is home to countless designer stores including Gucci and Dior. After a day of discovery, indulge in one of the many global restaurants and cuisines scattered throughout.

name: Canal View Studio Keizersgracht
description:
The Empress Studio is located in a unique romantic location in the heart of Amsterdam (the 'nine streets' area), with a great view on the Keizersgracht. The clean and stylish studio is on the ground floor, with a lovely terrace on the waterside. It is in the centre of Unesco's World Heritage Site and the major musea are 15 minutes on foot away.

The space
The Empress Studio is located in a typical Amsterdam merchant house from 1700. Its lower part was renovated in beautiful Jugendstil in 1900. neighborhood_overview:
The boat is moored at the Amstel River, the main canal of Amsterdam, on the edge of the Pijp neighborhood, one of the most cosmopolitan and vibrant districts of Amsterdam. You will find bars, restaurants, shops, the Albert Cuijp market and public transport around you at walking distance. Most places offer take-away food or food-on-order in case of a lock down.

A nice 15 to 20 minute walk along the Amstel River brings you to the central canal area and the major nightlife area Rembrandtplein, Hermitage Museum or Waterlooplein Flee market.

The boat is also a great starting point for exploring Amsterdam and its surroundings by boat or bike, for example to Ouderkerk aan de Amstel or Weesp. By car it takes half an hour to reach the North sea beach, the forests near Hilversum or the welcoming lakes of Loosdrecht.

neighborhood_overview: Traditionally a blue collar neighbourhood just a stone's throw away from the heart of town, 'De Baarsjes', is what one calls 'on the rise'. All around us we see new initiatives popping up; from intimate coffee bars and restaurants, to cool boutiques with local designers. Please ask the staff for inside info on where to go!
host_about:
Hotel Not Hotel is a place in Amsterdam where a room isn’t just a room, but a work of art with its own creator, story, and identity. Most of them designed and specially made by Collaboration-O, a group of young designers that originated from the Eindhoven Design Academy, and one by Arno Coenen and his partner IRIS.

When you wake up, you step into an art-filled, exhibition-like space instead of an anonymous lobby or hallway. The entire hotel is one big living room, with cosy seating areas between the cottages. Combined with our luxury beds and other facilities, Hotel Not Hotel offers an unrivalled experience. 
Besides all this, we feel that the value of a city lies in experiencing its local day-to-day life. As we are closely connected to Amsterdam and its numerous creative entrepreneurs, we know where to send you for a night on the town, a hidden culinary gem, or an upcoming artist’s exhibition. 

The bar connected to Hotel Not Hotel is called Kevin Bacon. Just like the actor, the bar has zero pretention, it always delivers, and it makes sure everybody has a good time.

Kevin Bacon is not your typical hotel bar. It’s where locals get their morning coffee or a quick breakfast. It’s where friends meet for a cocktail or a beer before diving into the nightlife, and where hotel guests let their hair down after a long day in the city.

When the weather is good, the ‘Whitey the White’ terrace is sunny like a perfectly fried egg. The staff’s friendly attitude shines all year round.

Amsterdam East, or simply Oost (pronounced ‘oast'), is an incredibly diverse district of Amsterdam that encompasses neighbourhoods that couldn't be more different from one another. Dapperbuurt hosts a huge market on one of the few streets in the region not named after an Indonesian island and is the ideal locale to try a Moroccan cookie or a real Turkish kebab.

There is a beach very nearby with a nice bistro that offers a view over the water, a fireplace and sometimes life music.
There is plenty parking space on the streets in the neighborhood but it's all paid. A 24h parkingticket comes at about 25 euro's. A 20 minute trip with tram will take you to the city center and trams leave nearby and frequently. A Night bus service from the Central Station to the ship is also available for those that favor the small hours.

description:
+++EXTRA CORONA INFO+++

1. More flexible reservation policy!
2. Safety first! The virus won't stand a change. The whole site is cleaned out even more thorough than what we're known for.
3. We’ve recently fully renewed the kitchen. Heat up that take away/ delivery or prepare a meal yourself!
4. We’ve got free parking in front of our other house at 20 min from the apt.

Looking forward to welcome you :) x Mimi

The space
Originally build around 1870, full of historic and original features, top floor with all that a visitor demands. Feel like a local! Perfect for a couple, bathroom an suite. 100% private. Use of kitchen and living. Within walking distance of all the major sightseeing.

Situated in the heart of Amsterdam; Central Station, Dam square, Royal Palace, Anne Frank Museum, Jordan Area and many other highlights, a heartbeat away. Vibrant night live around the corner but still a quite night rest.
neighborhood_overview:
During the 'Golden Century', a gold bank stood right at the center of Amsterdam. Behind this bank once was an alley. After the Tulip-boom the bank went bankrupt and had to break up the land the alley once was and sold it separately. At one side a little house was erected with room for a small shop at the ground floor and tree floors of living space on top. For over a century it was used in this way. But, after refurbishing it to today standards, the two top floors are now available for rent!

Located 5 min from: Dam, Anne Frank House, Jordan Area, Red Light District, 9 streets, trams to all directions.
host_about:
My name is Mimi. I rent this lovely building down town in Amsterdam.
I'm a goldsmith and jewelry designer. First floor is my shop where people can find all sorts of gifts. Hope to see you soon!

Our apartment in Oud West is in a very nice and quiet street near the beautiful Vondel Park. Not touristy, so you will feel like a local. There is a Tram stop literally around the corner.
Enjoy the eclectic mix of Oud-West at the district's most popular terraces, known for good drinks and reasonably-priced food. If you are the sporty type you can also go for a run in the Vondelpark or just lay on the grass and enjoy the greenery - perfect for people watching.

The Houthaven (Amsterdam) is a neighborhood of the city of Amsterdam, literally meaning 'lumber port'. The Houthaven is a port situated along the IJ river in Amsterdam's western port. Closely connected to the Jordaan and the famous canals of Amsterdam.
host_about:

Sjoerd

neighborhood_overview:
Rivierenbuurt is a neighbourhood of Amsterdam, Netherlands. The neighbourhood is situated in the eastern part of the borough of Amsterdam-Zuid, bordered by the river Amstel to the east, the Boerenwetering canal in the west, the Amstelkanaal in the north and the A10 motorway in the south. In 2013, the Rivierenbuurt had approximately 28,400 residents.[1]

The Rivierenbuurt was built in the 1920s as a primarily middle-class residential area, part of the Plan Zuid urban expansion programme designed by Dutch architect Hendrik Petrus Berlage.[2] The neighbourhood features many fine examples of Amsterdam School architecture. The Dutch word Rivierenbuurt translates as 'Rivers Neighbourhood', which refers to the fact that most streets in the area are named after rivers in the Netherlands.

name: Comfortable & bright houseboat in centre Amsterdam
description:
Stylish, bright and comfortable houseboat in the city center, suitable for up to three adults or 2 adults and two children. Staying here is a unique, authentic Amsterdam experience.
The boat is located in a small canal in the quiet part of Amsterdam's city center, but on walking distance of all sights as the Hermitage, the Rijksmuseum, the Rembrandtsquare, Dam Square and the Nieuwmarkt (Red Light Area).
We live in the houseboat, so you'll be staying in our home. We hope you'll love it!

The space
The living area is bright and spacious with a great view over the water. Breakfast at the large window dining table offers a glimpse into the spectacular life of the ducks, geese, swans, grebes, and coots.

Amsterdam is currently at its best. Few tourists in the center of Amsterdam, so it is fairly quiet and you have plenty of time to view all those beautiful old canal houses. What you have to pay attention to is that you reserve a restaurant or lunch
neighborhood_overview:
Just around the corner (2 to 5 minutes walking) are many nice bars and restaurants.

Have breakfast at Bagels & Beans at 2 minutes walk from the houseboat. Lunch at my personal favorite "De Hoftuin" located at the backside of the Hermitage museum, or take your lunch-to-go and eat it in the secret garden of the Royal Zoo Artis (5 minutes walk).

description:
Actually, I wanted to spend even more on each room, the furniture, the decoration and the many details... my husband and I just didn't seem to be on the same page. But I love my little hideaway in the middle of Amsterdam. Our neighbours in this place full of history are all native ones. Lawyers, midwives, judges, journalists and creative people live here close together - right in the city centre and yet away from the noise and bustle of the unbelievably many tourists.

The space
I want to give you a sense of "home" in these rooms. Modern, high-quality furnishings, designer pieces and especially many small details selected with love. Whenever I have found great pieces at a flea market again, I hope that you as guests will enjoy them.

In addition to the large terrace for all guests on the second floor, there is also the communal kitchen on the ground floor right at the entrance (then you do not have to carry the groceries far!) There is a record player -
neighborhood_overview:
Living by the canal - that is a dream for many. In the past, however, this was considered frowned upon and not classical enough. Therefore the canal was filled up around 16th century. A beautiful park in the middle of the city was created - and still is today. Large trees that provide shade in summer and absorb the sounds of the city.
I love the Cafe Slijterij Oosterling (50m from us). Open since 1877, this is probably one of the most authentic places in Amsterdam. Time seems to stand still here. If you are hungry, you can get delicious sandwiches, burgers, salads or freshly caught fish in the Brasserie Nel (400m). If you prefer self-catering and our shared kitchen, the supermarket is only 70m away.

Kinkerstraat is a multicultural area with a large shopping street filled with bars, restaurants, clothes etc. It’s criss-crossed with commercial streets, including Overtoom which has become a major interiors boulevard. Two of the city’s more interesting alternative cultural complexes, OT301 and Lab111, which both mix music, film and art, are located here. But for a real taste for the relaxed diversity of this neighbourhood, visit the sprawling terrace of Du Cap to truly witness all walks of life. And again: the whole city is pretty much nearby.

host_about:
Hi, my name is Heleen and I live my (mostly) happy life in Amsterdam with my partner and two daughters.  I came to his city in 1982 and probably will never leave anymore. I love my city, my house, my family, my friends and many other things. Really Amsterdam, ‘ the biggest village on earth’, offers so many beautiful things. We love to bike down town for coffee, shopping at the organic Noord Market or the so called Nine Streets, strolling in the Vondelpark, going to Paradiso or theatre with our daughters.  Many times we feel like tourists in our own town! 
I was educated as teacher French and Dutch but switched to the fashion industry as there was not enough work in teaching at that time. As a fashion agent I sell woman clothes to shops. As my business becomes more difficult the last year I decided to start b&b, and I love it. 
I also love to go hiking in the Alps or reading my books in our beach hut  at half an hour from where we live. 
I love going to cinema especially documentaries and art house films, and: yoga, meeting family and friends.

If you stay with us, there is a big chance that you meet my partner Karel as well. His work is project manager for art in public space. He is even a more enthousiatic mountaineer as I am: he also loves to climb the rocks as well. And when I am reading my book he is a probably out for sailing on the sea in his Laser. 
 
My two daughters can give you the best advices where to spend your money with shopping. They are working hard at school and dreaming and saving money for their round-the-world-trip within a few years.

Our two cats like sleeping very much.

At the end of the market you are right by the Heineken experience where you can take a tour and learn about the famous company and sample some of its finest beers. Right in front of the museum you can take a canal tour by boat, great experience in summer and winter alike. The famous Van Gogh museum is just behind and don't forget the modern art museum

neighborhood_overview:
The Amsterdam Canal District is a neighborhood in Amsterdam, Netherlands. The seventeenth-century canals of Amsterdam, located in the center of Amsterdam, were added to the UNESCO World Heritage List in August 2010. The Amsterdam Canal District consists of the area around the city’s four main canals: Singel, Herengracht, Keizersgracht, and Prinsengracht. From Brouwersgracht, the canals are generally parallel with one another, leading gradually southeast into the Amstel river.

Many of the canal houses in the Amsterdam Canal District are from the Dutch Golden Age in the 18th century. Many of these buildings, however, underwent restoration or reconstruction in various centuries, meaning that these building display many different architectural styles and facades.

The Foodhallen (with food court) and supermarkets are right around the corner and the famous Leidseplein is only a 10 minute walk.
You will have access to the whole apartment which has a bedroom, a large kitchen, a large living room and balcony.

The space
This luxurious apartment is right near the heart of the city. It has 2 comfortable beds in the master bedroom. For the third and fourth person there are two comfortable sleep couches in the large living room. neighborhood_overview: The area where the apartment is situated is one of the nicest and most upcoming areas in Amsterdam. The location is really perfect, in just 1 minute walk you have the Foodhallen, Ten Kate Market (around the corner), the best restaurants, trendy bars and coffee places. Shops and supermarket are just around the corner too. Within a 10-15 min walk you will be right in the heart of the city center. Van Gogh Museum, Rijksmuseum, Leidseplein and Vondelpark are not far from the apartment, just a 5-10 min bike ride. If you'd like to visit Anne Frank's house, please be sure to book tickets online as soon as possible, since they are sold out a long time in advance.

name: Beautiful Townhouse in the heart of Amsterdam!
description:
Welcome to our beautiful townhouse in the heart of Amsterdam!

We are a family of five living in the center of Amsterdam in a townhouse originally built in 1880 by Pierre Cuijpers, the architect of the Rijksmuseum. The house is spacious, light and comfortable, and is perfectly located for exploring Amsterdam. You can walk to Museum Square, the Leidseplein and the Canals. The Vondelpark is around the corner, as are all the amenities you might need (eg restaurants, supermarket, bakery, Starbucks)

The space
Our house is located on one of the most beautiful streets in Amsterdam with amazing architecture from the late 19th century and lots of trees.

Our home is very spacious and light, with large windows and high ceilings. The ground floor has a living room and open kitchen with dining room table. There is a TV with premium cable (Ziggo) and Netflix, as well as a fireplace and piano. There is a patio / terrace at the back of the house where guest
neighborhood_overview:
Our home is located in a part of Amsterdam that is called the Vondelbuurt, named after the Vondelpark which is borders. Green leafy streets and beautiful architecture make this one of the most sought after neighbourhoods in Amsterdam.

The location is quiet yet centrally located. Some of the main sites in walking distance:
- Vondelpark (250 meters)
- Leidseplein (450 meters)
- Museum Square (700 meters), which includes the Van Gogh, Stedelijk and Rijks Museums
- Canals (700 meters)

All amenities you might need are also nearby:
- Drug store (200 meters)
- Starbucks (and several other coffee shops) (250 meters)
- Supermarkets (Jumbo and Albert Heijn) (250 meters)
- Bakery (Vlaamsch Broodhuys) (350 meters)
- ... and many restaurants!

name: Amazing houseboat at the IJ!
description:
Our houseboat is a very authentic houseboat, very close by the city centre of Amsterdam. Amazing view on the water, very close to the hotspots of the Jordaan but also very relaxed and quiet.

A typical family boat!
Living room with sitting area, TV (netflix!), fireplace, and acces to the terrace in front of the boat. Kitchen, sitting table for 6-8, acces to the second terrace in front, sundeck!1 large bedroom, with double bed. Other bedroom with 2 separate beds. bathroom wth shower and WC.

The space
Our boat is a family boat! since we lived here, in 2013, we just started to rent out the captains cabin, the B&B. As we are fond of traveling we also rent out our own space, and it is nice to have guests over and meet new people.

The boat is a boat, not a house or apartment, so whenever it's windy and stormy, the boat rocks! When entering the boat, you'll have a private, indoor terrace. It's nice to sit there in the evening, we like to sit t
neighborhood_overview:
The neighbourhood is very quiet, because it's a Dam you don't have the go-through travel. Very close to the Jordaan area and to the Central Station. Plenty of options to eat/shop/visit!
In the beginning of the street: fresh croissants and the coffeespot. In the weekend there'a a truck-bakery from 8:30 till 9:30 for fresh bread.
host_about:
Eltjo works has his own company with cbd-products and Liselore en is setting up a bussiness with handmade clothes and accessories from Bali. We have 3 boys, in the age of 8,6 and the little one is 2 years old.

In 2013 we bought the boat " The Calidris". The main reason to live on a boat was to stay in the city, but still had enough space and above all, freedom. It feels like a little community in this street, because the boat people hang out together, help eachother and know eachother well.

We are very happy to live in such a special place in Amsterdam, enough space, nice views, but still connected to the city! We like cooking together, traveling with our 3 boys, designing our home or making trips with our camper.

In 2014 we started our B&B. Where you sleep now, it used to be the captain's cabin. We immediately removed the stairs, so we do not miss the space at all. It as always a dream for me to run a little boutique hotel. Nowadays we don't run a hotel, but a pittoresque B&B, which we really enjoy. It is fun to meet people all over the world who mostly have a great time at our boat. When you would like to see how houseboat-people live just knock on the door and we will show you around!

Enjoy your stay!


Eltjo

description:
Located in super central A-location, across from Amsterdam CS in walking distance of Dam Square. This characteristic and spacious apartment is located in a 16th century building and comes with 2 bedrooms and 1,5 bathrooms.

Under Amsterdam City Council law we can only host more than 4 people, when they are from the same family or household.

* Contact us for special requirements or off-season specials. *

The space
This is your chance to stay in one of the oldest historic buildings, in the heart of Amsterdam's City Centre, situated on the beautiful and famous Singel canal.

This beautiful 90m2/970ft apartment, is situated in a 17th century building which is listed on the UNESCO World Heritage list. The property has a beautiful stepped gable, old doors and large original wooden beams. Through these authentic details, you will feel like you are staying in the heart of old historic Amsterdam.

This 'boutique hotel-feel’,
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is very centrally located within walking distance of and across from Amsterdam Central Station (350 meters), on the corner of the Haarlemmerstraat, (recently voted best shopping street of the Netherlands 2012), with its charming shops and cafes. It is located within walking distance of the city centre attractions such as the Dam Square, Beurs van Berlage, Madame Tussaud and Jordaan area. Museums, theatres and night-life can all be found on your doorstep.

There are a few parking options.
By booking your parking online you can stay 24 or 48 hrs (Max!) for only € 20,- or € 40,-
You can book via :
(website hidden)

The other option is you park your car at the Park&Ride at Zeeburg which is just out of the centre. It only cost a € 8,- per day. You'll get 8 free public transport tickets. The tramline #26 will bring you right back into the centre (stop
host_about:
Hello, we’re Esther & Jan! 

Esther is a business professional, working in the field of sustainability and has lived overseas in countries such as; Aruba, Bonaire, Spain, Australia and New Zealand. Jan is an entrepeneur in the Restaurant & Hospitality industry and has lived in Amsterdam for 25 years. Together we have 2 young kids.  We both share a passion for good food and great wines and love to travel (preferably with AirBNB). Since we feel personal contact is very important  we do not work with an hosting agency, but we do everything ourselves. We will be on site to personally meet you upon arrival for your check in and will be available 24/7 during your stay.  We enjoy meeting new people and having both worked in the tourism &  hospitality industry, we want to ensure you will have a fantastic time in Amsterdam!  



So please do not hesitate to contact us with any of your questions or special requests and we'll try to answer them & help you out as soon as possible!  

** Please note Kobalt Inn are official Short-stay apartments. This means we pay city and tourist tax, we have permits and and are registered at the Chamber of Commerce. We can only accept more than 2 adults per apartment when they are from the same family or household. We have 2 apartments and per apartment we can accommodate families with up to a maximum of 4 children **

name: Sleeping under Stars in Rural Amsterdam
description:
Sleeping under Stars & Free Parking! Authentic restored dike house from 1903, situated on the Schellingwouderdijk in Amsterdam. The beautiful surroundings are a perfect combination for people that love both the City Center and Rural Life. The characteristic Family House offers views on the Amsterdam IJ and meadow for children to play, with tables from where to enjoy the panoramic sight of horses and ships sailing by. In summer swim in front, skate in winter! Registered under 97188. Z/20/1761348

The space
Master bedroom for two persons. (Possibility to include additional room if 4 persons -see my other advertisements). Perfect for couples or families.

Dining room with coffeemachine, cooking facilities, fridge, dishwasher, oven and microwave available on request.

Picknick tables in front of the house with view on Amsterdam IJ and meadow with horses.

Various restaurants, (sustainable/organic) grocery stores, supermarkets and bakerie
neighborhood_overview:
Schellingwoude is a former Fishing-village in the Northern part of Amsterdam. The Monumental Dike is situated between meadows, park and the IJ, with the City Centre just at the other side of the water. Various (sustainable/organic) grocery stores, supermarkets and bakeries are at walking distance.

A perfect area for cycling, Marken and Volendam are a 30 minute bike-ride along the dike, Edam and Monnikendam are at the distance of an hour by bike through beautiful meadows with horses, cows and sheep. One can have a break or High Tea in one of the authentic Cafes or a glass of biological milk, or biological ice-cream in a farm on the way. Excellent (sustainable) restaurants in both the rural countryside and in the artistic part of Northern Amsterdam - De Ceuvel, Pllek, Il Pecorino, Wilhelmina Dok (with views on the large cruiseships), Loetje, De Goudfazant, etc. Or one can have a cool beer or white wine on a terrace at Het Sluisje, Het Schoolhuis, Beer Brewery Oedipus, Landmark

neighborhood_overview:
The modest origins of the Jordaan (it was built to house Jewish and French immigrant workers) is still visible in its small, very old houses and the fact there is an old cafe on nearly every corner (often the type where locals will burst into folk music on Sunday drinking sessions). Nowadays these old brown cafes share space with brick oven pizzerias, boutique design shops and other trappings of the young professional set.
Nice to know: each of the streets is named after a flower.

neighborhood_overview:
Within minutes of walking in the other direction you enter De Jordaan, originally a working-class neighbourhood, but now the most famous area of Amsterdam. Its heart is formed by what is known to locals as ‘The Nine Streets’. These small and charming streets are overflowing with vintage and designer shops, specialty stores, art galleries, cosy cafés and great little restaurants of almost every kind you can think of. Walking through these streets you will hear the bells of the Westertoren – the same ones Anne Frank described in her diary, while in hiding during the Second World War. Visiting the world famous Anne Frank House, now a biographical museum, offers an unforgettable experience.

Many houses in De Jordaan have inner courtyards, built by rich people for elderly women, which are lovely to visit. There are three markets; one at the Westerstraat, one at the Lindengracht and last but not least: De Noordermarkt, the oldest and most beautiful organic farmer’s market, everyon

The room is located on the 1st floor (no steep stairs).

The space
This room and bathroom are completely private. It has a twin bed on a typical Dutch ''vide'' (an extra floor within a room) which gives a really fun, cosy experience to your stay, the room has enough closet space, WIFI. Guest access
We share the frontdoor

There are multiple places to enjoy a nice breakfast or a drink and there is a big supermarket. Central Station, Rembrandt square, Dam square and the Hermitage are all on short walking distance (10 minutes). Just around the corner of the apartment you find the Botanical Gardens, the lovely Waterloo market and the National Maritime Museum for example.

neighborhood_overview: The farmhouse is located in a green area of Amsterdam. On the west and east side there are small fields with my goats and sheep. North is the Haarlemmerweg, the exit road to Amsterdam, Haarlem, Alkmaar and The Hague. The nature reserve "De Bretten" is also to the north. To the south is the sports park where you can play tennis and there are annual rugby matches held at a global level. De Farmhouse is located in  "Tuinen van West" nature and recreation area. This area is located in a regional greenstructure and is therefore particularly animal and plant species rich. In the Tuinen van West there are various restaurants and accesable fruit and vegetable growers as well as an organic supermarket. The recreation area is connected with various surrounding nature and recreational areas such as Spaarnwoude and Het Amstelland. From here you can cycle out of the city into the green. If you want more Nature then a trip to the North Holland dune area is recommended or to the Oostvaardersplassen.

Discover the beautiful and abundant city of Amsterdam from the heart of its historic city centre. Our newly renovated private suite is tucked away in a quiet alley next to Amsterdam’s main attractions and famous canals.

**Dear Guests, due to the COVID-19 I would like to share some information with you. We are open and hosting but are taking extra precautions due to the virus. Please read complete message at 'Guests Interaction'.**

The space
The house is rightfully part of the historic buildings in Amsterdam, being over a 100 years old and built in iconic Amsterdam style of that era. On the inside however, the house has been completely renovated in 2018.

The building consists of three small floors and the bottom floor has an entrance to the staircase of the building.
The third floor of the building covers your suite, which you reach through a winding staircase typical for a Dutch home. When you come up the stairs and reach the third f
neighborhood_overview: The moment you step out of the house, you’re standing in the heart of the historic city centre of Amsterdam. In this area you can find most of the city’s famous attractions and sights, such as the Dam Palace, museums, the flower market, the red light district, nightlife and still so much more to discover. Fortunately Amsterdam is not only known for its nightlife, but also for it’s extensive and longstanding culture. The Rembrandt house is right around the corner and the Anne Frank house is at a stone’s throw away. The city centre is the most historic part of Amsterdam, so you will be surrounded by the famous Amsterdam canals and the typical houses lined along them. The iconic architecture, decorative lights and bridges make the city centre the most romantic part of the city.

name: Stylish family apartment in the museums district
description:
Spacious and stylish family apartment in the Old South Amsterdam, 3 min walk from the Vondelpark with nearby grocery stores, cafes and restaurants. Tram stops at 50 meters giving easy access to the city center.
It is a bright apartment located on the 3rd floor. The living area and balcony are at the entrance level. 3 bedrooms, the main bathroom and the washing room are at the 4th floor; the 4th bedroom and a smaller bathroom are at the attic with access to a large terras, small kitchen and BBQ

The space
We would be happy to welcome you in our nice and cosy appartment. You will find all sorts of board games (mainly in dutch though), a piano and you will have access to Netflix.
We will leave some milk, coffee and cereals for your first breakfast.
I will send you some recommandations on nearby restaurants and places to go.
Our cleaning lady will be happy to come during your stay if this is convenient for you.

Guest access
neighborhood_overview: The Vondelpark is biggest parc of Amsterdam and is reachable within few minutes. We live in the ' old south' area, 15min walk from the museum district. You can find all types of cafes, restaurants and boutiques in the area.
host_about:

name: Amsterdam apartment in the middle of De Pijp
description:
Cozy, modern apartment in the middle of the popular area De Pijp. The space is great and everything you need and want to see is nearby. This is where you want to be when you visit Amsterdam!

The space
The 2 person apartment has a large living room with an open kitchen. In addition there is a bathroom with shower, washing machine and dryer, and a separate toilet. The bedroom has a double bed and air conditioning. The bed is raised (1 meter high) and can be easily accessed. There is also a balcony with large doors which can open up the entire back of the apartment. The apartment is around 50m2. The building is located in a typically old Amsterdam street.

Guest access
The entire apartment is accessible. Since I normally live there, I will make sure there is enough closet space available by emptying out some cabinets and locking a few filled with my personal belongings.

Other things to note
Note: it is absolutely not allo
neighborhood_overview: The apartment is located in a quiet, residential side street of a busy street, in the middle of the popular area De Pijp. De Pijp is filled with hip bars, restaurants, coffee places, shops and the famous Albert Cuyp Market (10 minute walk). There is plenty to do during the day as well as during the night. The nearest supermarket is only 40 meters away. Furthermore, tram 4 stops right in front of the apartment and will take you through the rest of the city center in minutes. It really is a great location.

description:

The space
This modern and spacious 90 m2 apartment makes for a comfortable stay in the lively Amsterdam-Oost neighborhood.

The ground floor features a large living room with two comfy sofas, a projector connected to Chromecast for Netflix and a big dining table. The kitchen comes with a dishwasher, large fridge and cooking appliances.

The balcony and stairs lead to the backyard garden with a terrace and pond.

On the bottom floor is the bedroom. There's a comfy Auping double bed. The bathroom has two sinks, a toilet and a bath with rain-shower.

Next to the bedroom is a small office space with a large desk to work on.
neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam-Oost has become one of city's most popular neighbourhoods with locals, due to the vast amount of fine cafes, bars and restaurants. Within walking distance are the famous Artis Zoo, Dappermarket, Oosterpark, Flevopark and Tropenmuseum.

host_about: Generator Amsterdam is located in the up-and-coming eastern side of the city, overlooking Oosterpark. This former zoological university building can accommodate 564 guests in 168 twin and quadruple rooms, with en-suite bathrooms and incredible views of the surrounding area. There is also one luxury apartment for six people, with views of the park and a self-catered kitchen. It has flexible and spacious social areas, filled with creative design touches like glass-fronted elevators, a light and airy café and an outdoor terrace. We’ve turned the former lecture hall into an impressive chill-out lounge and bar, while the old library is now a relaxation and private events room. The basement and café are now dining destinations and the original boiler room has become a secret late night bar.

The Oud-Zuid area used to be a upper-class neigherhood and still it's home to some of the most upscale and expensive homes in Amsterdam. It is a safe area. A lot of locals live here and it's home to plenty of art galleries, unique shops and restaurants. It's an upcoming area with nice places to go relax and chill in the evenings.

host_about:
I am a realtor since 20 years. Some of my hobbies are travelling,  Ibiza, (race) cycling, my work, cars, soccer and my close friends and family. 

We started this company 20 years ago. In April 2013 we started with renting out through Airbnb. With our experience in letting out to expats from the biggest Multinationals (Shell/Unilever/Johnson&Johnson) we know what people expect in a temporary apartment. 

We try to develop our apartments in a tasteful neutral style with high quality finishing and - furniture on nice locations like the Amsterdam Jordaan Area. Our apartments are not on the busiest places of Amsterdam but always on a maximum 3 minute walk from the canals. 

All our (Amsterdam)apartments are fully licensed by town hall what means that safety is on place 1. Infrared smoke detectors, flight plans, not too many people in 1 flat, no drugs etc.

We try to offer a hotel idea but than in an apartment. So more privacy, luxury, convenience and space on a AAA location but for a better price!

A definite no go is asking for a discount. If our prices are too high I would suggest to rent a bed where the owner was in the night before. 

Also we dont accept guests without any reviews. No exceptions. Sorry.


What is also convenient in our opinion is that we do not live our selves in the apartments. So You dont  sleep on a bed where someone has slept on for 5 years already. 

After every guest the apartments are professionally cleaned and so are  the towels and bedlinen by a professional company.

please see our reviews for confirmation if you are not convinced yet!

neighborhood_overview: Houthaven is a neighbourhood of Amsterdam, Netherlands situated in the West borough. Literally meaning "lumber port", Houthaven is a port situated along the IJ in Amsterdam's western port. It is bordered by a dam in the IJ river to the north and the Spaarndammerbuurt in the south. It is currently predominantly used by inland barges, however plans are in motion to radically change the area in the next few years by building a new residential area on seven artificial islands.

Spiegelkwartier

The Spiegelkwartier is the Art and Antiques district in Amsterdam.
Here you’ll find more than 70 antiques dealers and art galleries, together offering a resplendent array of fine historical objects, classic and contemporary art, and exotic folk art.
You will find also restaurants, casual eateries and cosy cafés on almost every corner.
The Spiegelkwartier is located between the Herengracht and the Rijksmuseum.

www.spiegelkwartier.nl

Museum Quarter

The Amsterdam Museum Quarter is home to the three most important museums in the Netherlands: the Rijksmuseum, the Stedelijk Museum and the Van Gogh Museum.
It also houses the majestic Concertgebouw and some superb cafés and restaurants.
With its large grassy open area, the Museumplein offers plenty of room to have a picnic or just relax. The Museum Quarter even has its own indoor swimming pool.

Residents live in the heart of the city - but that does mean avoiding the occasional wayward tourists on bicycles or revelling party-goers. With the building of the Amsterdam Public Library, one can not only enjoy one of Europe's largest public collections but also the expansive view of Amsterdam Centre from the roof-top café.

Hip and happening bars along Oosterpark and Java straat like Biertuin

Hannekes boom (nice hangout)

Amsterdam is a very quiet city compared to other major ones

neighborhood_overview: The Jordaan is a famous district in the center of Amsterdam. Originally it was a working-class neighborhood, but now the Jordaan is one of the most expensive locations in Amsterdam. Most of the streets and canals are named after flowers and trees. It is a cosy neighborhood with many traditional cafes, art galleries, modern art and specialty shops and restaurants. Many houses have inner courtyards, the courtyards were built by rich people for elderly women. There are 3 markets in this district; the Noordermarkt, there is a market at the Westerstraat and at the Lindengracht. Around these areas there are a lot of traditional cafes and bars. The world famous Anne Frank Huis is located in this district. It is a biographical museum dedicated to Anne Frank, who was a diarist during the Second World War.

name: 18th Century Groundfloor Canal House with patio
description:
With its picturesque canal view, rich history and modern design, this 2 floor house is a unique city destination. Each area of Amsterdam has its own character and charm. This listed monument dating back to the 18th century, and completely renovated, is truly a quiet retreat and a hidden treasure. Situated directly in the heart of the city, the oldest and most beautiful part of town, this canal house is part of Amsterdam’s iconic Canal Ring and listed as a UNESCO’s World Heritage Site. 

The space
“Home away from home” as our guests would say. Two floors of pure luxury in a great amount of privacy. The main entrance is at the charming Singel canal side. The entrance hall with typical high ceilings and authentic marble floor lead you into our spacious living room with lots of natural daylight and a private patio at the back side of the house. Connecting to the modern and well equipped kitchen with dining area at the front of the house, set the ambiance on the ground
neighborhood_overview:
The house is located on one of the major residential canals in the city centre. It is conveniently located near major tram-lines and only steps away from the Anne Frank House, Dam Square and the Jordaan, which is famous for its variety of shops, restaurants and galleries. The major museums: Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh and Stedelijk are within walking distance. Traveling with children? Visit NEMO (the largest science centre in the Netherlands), ARTIS Royal Zoo, Kinderkookcafé in the Vondelpark, Madame Tussauds or outside Amsterdam De Efteling, Dolfinarium or Madurodam. 
“A Narrow Strip of Dutch Cool”
That is what The New York Times called the Herenstraat and surrounded area. The neighbourhood became increasingly trendy (…) the quaint streets of Herenstraat and Prinsenstraat began to buzz with new energy. Trendy bars and innovative restaurants have opened. And a steady march of independent boutiques is turning the area into one of the city’s coolest retail strips.

Saskia and Michiel

name: Beautiful, Relaxing Apartment in Amsterdam.
description:
Welcome to my lovely apartment. This beautiful, light and comfortable space is conveniently located in Amsterdam city. A perfect place for couples or people on business trips. Literally across the street from RAI convention center and financial WTC, it is also surrounded by plenty of great restaurants, cozy brunch cafes, and the best ice cream shop of Amsterdam. Next door you can find the green and relaxing Beatrix Park. Just rent a bike next door and enjoy the full Amsterdam experience.

The space
The apartment is located in the Rivierenbuurt district in Amsterdam city. This neighborhood is well known for its beautiful architecture and familiar atmosphere. The location is ideally suited for couples or for business travelers.

The apartment has everything you might need to have a comfortable stay.

A fully equipped kitchen; Spacious and bright living and dining room ; A modern bathroom; A cosy balcony
The master bedroom has a queen si
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is situated in the picturesque Rivierenbuurt neighbourhood of Amsterdam. The neighbourhood is situated in Amsterdam-Zuid, bordered by the river Amstel to the east, the Boerenwetering canal in the west, the Amstelkanaal in the north and the A10 motorway in the south.

The neighbourhood features many fine examples of Amsterdam School-architecture. The Dutch word Rivierenbuurt translates as 'Rivers Neighbourhood', which refers to the fact that most streets in the area are named after rivers in the Netherlands.

The apartment is literally across the street from the RAI convention center, very close to the train station and the metro 52, which takes you to the busiest centre of Amsterdam, literally in 7 minutes.
The apartment is also situated across the street from the finest restaurants and bars (best fish restaurant in town!).
host_about:
I’m passionate and curious by nature. I really enjoy meeting and hosting new people at my place. 
love traveling, living in different places and experiencing new cultures... that’s why Amsterdam is the city to be in.
As hobbies, apart from traveling I love diving, cooking (with nice music on), reading  books, do some (amateur) oil painting or just  going for long walks and picnics in Beatrix park (just next to my house) ...
Also like decoration and making my house  nice and cozy.
With friends we often indulge in a grilled meat or fish meal in restaurants nearby accompanied by a cold bottle of white wine. 
For travel or for work, come and try the true Amsterdam life,  I have a bunch of good tips for you :) Have fun!

My house is situated in the picturesque  Rivierenbuurt neighbourhood of Amsterdam city. The neighbourhood is bordered by the river Amstel. 
The neighbourhood features many fine examples of Amsterdam School-architecture. The Dutch word Rivierenbuurt translates as 'Rivers Neighbourhood', refers to the fact that most streets in the area are named after rivers in the Netherlands.

Until World War II the area had a sizable Jewish population which included Anne Frank and her family, who lived at Merwedeplein square until they went into hiding in the secret annex located in the Jordan.

Two minutes walking around my house you can be served by tram routes that takes you everywhere  in the city, such 4 and 12, bus routes 62 and 65, as well as Amsterdam metro and the train from Schiphol Airport, Amstel Station and Zuid Station. But if you want to try the real Amsterdam life you can always rent a bike just next door.


I’m sure you will have an amazing time !

neighborhood_overview:
Our house is situated in a quiet residential area in Amsterdam-North. There are not many tourists here, but with the (free) ferry you are in downtown Amsterdam within 20 minutes. An excellent place to escape the crowdy parts to make the most of your stay.

Practical information:
* There is a supermarket at walking distance. It is called Plus and you’ll find it at the end of the street. It’s open till 8 P.M. More supermarkets and food shops you’ll find at the mall called Banne Buiksloot or Molenwijk, which is a 20 minutes’ walk. For the best bread & fresh croissants you can go to a nice bakery called BROOD which is located near the NDSM ferry. There is also a weekly market on the Van Der Pekstraat (wed, fri & sat). Here you can buy cheap, fresh products. For the market take bus 35 till central station, bus stop Mosplein.

Things to do and see:
In Amsterdam-North:
* You are close to the NDSM wharf, where you will find a couple of restaurants and bars
