Within a 2 minute walk you can find an amazing bakery, coffee house, supermarkets, wine store, fish mongers, butchers, florist, bike shop and a host of restaurants.

Within a 5 minute walk you’ll find plenty of bars that serve fantastic locally brewed beers and gins as well as tasty Dutch bar snacks.

Within a 10 minute walk you’ll be in heart of the Amsterdam canal rings, along side the Westerkerk, Ann Frank house, the 9 Streets and the bustling Jordaan district.

Upon booking the apartment we can provide you with our favourite spots to eat, drink and relax away from the busy tourist spots.
host_about:
Englishman living in Amsterdam, often travelling with my partner who's from the US. On a mission to see the world, either through a city break in Europe or back-packing through Asia for weeks at a time.

Working for Nike at their European HQ in the Netherlands.
Outside of work, life revolves around home the comforts; cooking, cycling and sailing around Amsterdam, walking the dog.

Ultimate holiday destination: Japan

name: White Houseboat Prinsengracht
description:
The space
From the houseboat you are at few minutes walk from Anne Frank's house and Westerchurch. You are surrounded by nice restaurants, galeries and boutiques. On the corner is a supermarket that is opened 7 days a week. Inside the houseboat you find a bright, tastefully furnished living with windows all around overlooking the canal, a fully equiped modern open plan kitchen, a washing machine, a separate bedroom with a comfortable double bed, a bathroom and toilet. The extra luxury is your private terrace overlooking the water. After a day exploring the city, you can sit outside, relax and enjoy the ducks swimming towards you to say hello. Come and stay on this fantastic location: historical, central and yet quiet and safe, and enjoy the feeling of living like an Amsterdam local in your private houseboat

Other things to note
We can let you know about tours, get you a private boat, bikes, guest listed, let you know about local parties, art openings,
neighborhood_overview: The area is full of shops and restaurants. It is in the center of Amsterdam. From the apartment you can walk within 10 minutes to the Rembrandtplein square, in 15 minutes to the Leidseplein square and the Dam square.
host_about:
This was a truly unique experience to stay on a houseboat. I grew up in Amsterdam but never had the opportunity to stay or even visit a houseboat. I stayed here for 10 days at the end of April and was very fortunate to be blessed with great weather. My stay was excellent and the houseboat contributed a large part to that. It is located in one of the best locations of the city: next to the Jordaan and close to the Westermarkt (with Anne Frank house). It is very quiet on the water even though the city is hustling around you. Sitting outside, looking out over the water is a great experience. Weekends the canal is a bit busier with lots of small boats coming through but it create a unique atmosphere that you will not find in any of the hotels. The houseboat itself is unique so it is hard to describe, it is not small, but it does create an intimate atmosphere. I can see it would be great for a romantic stay (even though I stayed alone Lachebekje (zwart-wit)). The layout makes that the sleeping part is separated from the kitchen/living part even though there are no doors between the sections. The bed is excellent, the shower strong and hot, the kitchen fully equipped, lots of books to read and music to play. But most of the time you will be sitting outside enjoying the view of the canal and the sounds of the city. The nights and morning could be a bit chilly but heather worked just fine. I would recommend the houseboat to anyone who would like ta truly unique Amsterdam experience.
May 2014 Werner CFO Amazon

What an amazing boat and location! We spent most of our visit sitting on the back deck...and watching the symphony of the city happen around us. The bed was comfy (and I am picky), the fresh flowers were nice. We also enjoyed feeding the momma and daddy ducks with their babies. We will return and we hope the boat is available when we do.
July 2014 Eillen

What an amazing boat and location! We spent most of our visit sitting on the back deck...and watching the symphony of the city happen around us.  July 2014 Heike and Günther

The houseboat was awesome - everything we expected. Fake was a wonderful hosts and the houseboat had everything we needed. We had a small problem with the heat and Fake came over so quickly. It was really a simple button to reset that was all but I hadn't figured it out. The location is fantastic too - really I think best neighborhood in Amsterdam. What a treat to experience Amsterdam this way. I highly recommend it.
december 2013 Betty and Mike

El houseboat fue realmente muy confortable , conseguía que te sintieras como en casa y el lugar donde esta situado es simplemente espectacular, cerca de restaurantes, tiendas - se hace hasta un mercado semanal en la zona donde comprar productos de alimentación frescos, bio.....etc Una familia de patos te visita cada día y se mueren por el pan!!!
August 2014 Hellen

Es war alles perfekt, die Fotos geben das Boot realistisch wider, Fake war zuverlässig und sehr nett im Kontakt, der Besitzer sehr serviceorientiert und freundlich. Das Bett ist sehr komfortabel, die Ausstattung völlig ausreichend. Die Lage ist wirklich absolut zentral und alles ist fußläufig gut erreichbar. Wir könne die Unterkunft auf jeden Fall weiterempfehlen und werden wiederkommen, wenn das Boot frei ist. 
August 2014 Tina und Ute





Rugby A.S.R.V Ascrum - member since 1989
Kiwanis Amsterdam member since 2005

neighborhood_overview:
The area we live in is called HOOFDDORPPLEINBUURT. I live here now for 30 years and have seen the neigbourhood change in a pleasant cozy area. Lots of shops, cafés, restaurants just a few minutes from our place.
It is a safe, quiet, but vibrant area with families with young children, elderly and students, a pleasant mixture of all coulorful people.
host_about:
I am a proud citizen of Amsterdam since 1987. In 2001 I started hosting guests in my garden room. Guests from all over the world stayed here. 
I traveled the world the last 30 years because of my work and know how important it is to feel at home when you are away from home.
I believe in changing the world to a better world by starting here and now, making the change. I love to do yoga and workout in the gym, go for a run or bike ride. We do not have a car.
In 2015 we installed 13 solar panels on the roof, in 2016 another 6 solar panels. We have renovated a big part of our 6 stories house: 75 % of the windows are isolated, we have a hot water regain installation on the top floors, a water descaling machine for the entire house (descaled water reduces the use of detergents and soaps/shampoos and extends the lifetime of washing machine and dish washer).
Our family is  non-smoking and  vegetarian and partly vegetarian, because we think it contributes to a better, cleaner and more sustainable world
We  believe in personal, mindful and sustainable, eco friendly tourism: enjoy our beautiful city with respect for the environment,   inhabitants and other visitors of Amsterdam.

neighborhood_overview:
The Amsterdam Jordaan is undoubtedly the most sung about, described and romanched town district of the Netherlands. Today it is a favorite place for students, artists and young profesionals. This charming neighborhood is Amsterdam's Greenwich Village, with its narrow alleys, leafy canals lined with 17th-century houses, quirky specialty shops, cafes and designer boutiques. More info: http://www.jordaaninfo.com/
The noordermarkt hosts one of the best flea and food market in Amsterdam. Every Saturday and Monday morning, many local people come to this part of town to enjoy its wonderful atmosphere. The area is also one of the most popular for going out in one of the many cafe in the area.

name: AMAZING NEW LUXURY SAILINGBOAT ACCOMMODATION
description:
"Sailing barge Egberdina" is over a century old. During her long life she has explored the Dutch waters carrying cargo and goods from one place to the next.

Nowadays she has been refitted to accommodate groups of passengers. With a luxury design that is reminiscent of the early 1900's, she provides a place to stay, unwind and relax.

The atmosphere makes you wonder about the adventures of earlier days, the life people must have lived and all the unknown shores this ship must have visited..

The space
Egberdina is designed in the style of the period when it was build, the early 1900's. We have furnished this design by adding comfortable Bohemian elements while retaining a spacious atmosphere on the boat.

There are no separate cabins or rooms. Rather we have chosen to create areas. This means that there is less privacy between guests but more space in the boats interior.

Egberdina is divided into three sections.
neighborhood_overview:
The Eastern islands of IJburg are a Wonderfull place in Amsterdam. They are located to the east of Amsterdam and provide excellent accessibility of the historic city centre as well as the beaches out to the east.

The tram that takes you to Amsterdam central station in 17 minutes stops at a distance of about 4 mins walk.

The beach club of Blijburg is located at a 15 minute walk and the beaches of the IJ-lake or the Amsterdam lakeside are right around the corner at a distance of 5 mins walking.

There is a lovely boulevard with greats restaurants and bares located right in front of the boat as well as several companies that rent out gear for watersports.

Ijburg is a lively community that provides it all, water, beaches, sports and activities as well as a direct connection to the historic city centre of Amsterdam.

Welcome! This apartment is very well located directly on the Prinsengracht canal with a wonderful view of the canals from the big windows in the living room. There is a living room with a fully equipped open kitchen. There are two bedrooms on the backside of the apartment, nice for a good night's sleep. We are within walking distance from the historical city centre and big cultural must-see's such as Rijksmuseum & Van Gogh museum. It's the perfect location for your Amsterdam stay!

The space
What makes this apartment unique, are the three big windows on the canal side which gives the room so much daylight and a great view. There are no other houses/buildings across the street, only a small square and some trees (which bloom beautifully in spring). The apartment is located right in the centre/on canals, but it's still very quiet. With the bedrooms located on the backside of the apartment, you will experience no traffic noise at night.

Guest access
neighborhood_overview: You will find everything you need for a pleasant stay right around the corner of the apartment. Two supermarkets are within walking distance, just like bars, shops in the lovely Utrechtsestraat or Leidsestraat, Van Gogh museum and Rijksmuseum. The Prinsengracht canal area is so typical and atmospheric, enjoy a nice walk around the area and really get to know the neighborhood. Or even better, experience it like a local and hire bikes!

description:
Industrial style small apartment-studio in the most trendy area of Amsterdam; North. Located in one of the most interesting and new developing areas. If you are into architecture, free style-design, usage of non traditional materials, this is the "original" street and place to be, where the new development started. On 10 minutes from central station and city centre, walking distance to the hip NDSM area, nice restaurants, public transport and we have rental bikes on the site!

The space
Our apartment-studio (30m2), in industrial & light style, is located on the ground-floor of our own designed & build house, with all facilities for yourself, including private entrance.

description:
This house is located in a unique pittoresque little street with no tall buildings, in the upcoming De Baarsjes neighborhood, west of the center. There’s a big garden in the back with lots of sun until the evening.
Perfect for couples or families.

The space
This house is located in a unique pittoresque little street without any tall buildings, in the upcoming De Baarsjes neighborhood, west of the center. There’s a big garden in the back with lots of sun until the evening.
The house is in the center of all the action, with both the Jordaan and the Vondelpark a 10- minute walk away. Perfect for couples or families.

Even though the area is getting more popular, one of the assets of this house is the quietness in the lush garden where you won’t notice you are actually in the middle of the city. The street is quiet because it’s mostly used by cyclists.

name: Tiny design house at ground floor with garden
description:
Welcome in my tiny house! 39m2 but all the space you need for a pleasant stay in beautiful Amsterdam. In 2018 I bought this little house and renovated it together with my father. With a lot of love and fun I was able to make it the way I want it to be. I have even been in a magazine with my house.
With a bathroom en-suite and a spacious living room with open kitchen it has all the luxury you need. Bus and tram stop are in front of the door and take you to the city centre within 10 minutes :)

The space
Het huisje is uniek omdat het een hoekwoning is met maar 1 directe buurwoning, en dus geen boven- en onderburen, én een tuin! Daarnaast is alles op de begane grond en heeft het een eigen voordeur. Ik heb de woning zelf verbouwd in 2018, nadat ik de woning casco opgeleverd kreeg. Elektra, water, wanden.. alles moest nog gedaan worden en dat gaf mij de vrijheid om het helemaal naar wens te maken en zo efficiënt mogelijk in te delen.
